38/* Some local macros to save typing. Undef'd at the end. */
39#define IR(ref) (&J->cur.ir[(ref)])
40
41/* Pass IR on to next optimization in chain (FOLD). */
42#define emitir(ot, a, b) (lj_ir_set(J, (ot), (a), (b)), lj_opt_fold(J))
43
44/* Emit raw IR without passing through optimizations. */
45#define emitir_raw(ot, a, b) (lj_ir_set(J, (ot), (a), (b)), lj_ir_emit(J))
46
47/* -- Sanity checks ------------------------------------------------------- */
48
49#ifdef LUA_USE_ASSERT
50/* Sanity check the whole IR -- sloooow. */
51static void rec_check_ir(jit_State *J)
52{
53 IRRef i, nins = J->cur.nins, nk = J->cur.nk;
54 lj_assertJ(nk <= REF_BIAS && nins >= REF_BIAS && nins < 65536,
55 "inconsistent IR layout");
56 for (i = nk; i < nins; i++) {
57 IRIns *ir = IR(i);
58 uint32_t mode = lj_ir_mode[ir->o];
59 IRRef op1 = ir->op1;
60 IRRef op2 = ir->op2;
61 const char *err = NULL;
62 switch (irm_op1(mode)) {
63 case IRMnone:
64 if (op1 != 0) err = "IRMnone op1 used";
65 break;
66 case IRMref:
67 if (op1 < nk || (i >= REF_BIAS ? op1 >= i : op1 <= i))
68 err = "IRMref op1 out of range";
69 break;
70 case IRMlit: break;
71 case IRMcst:
72 if (i >= REF_BIAS) { err = "constant in IR range"; break; }
73 if (irt_is64(ir->t) && ir->o != IR_KNULL)
74 i++;
75 continue;
76 }
77 switch (irm_op2(mode)) {
78 case IRMnone:
79 if (op2) err = "IRMnone op2 used";
80 break;
81 case IRMref:
82 if (op2 < nk || (i >= REF_BIAS ? op2 >= i : op2 <= i))
83 err = "IRMref op2 out of range";
84 break;
85 case IRMlit: break;
86 case IRMcst: err = "IRMcst op2"; break;
87 }
88 if (!err && ir->prev) {
89 if (ir->prev < nk || (i >= REF_BIAS ? ir->prev >= i : ir->prev <= i))
90 err = "chain out of range";
91 else if (ir->o != IR_NOP && IR(ir->prev)->o != ir->o)
92 err = "chain to different op";
93 }
94 lj_assertJ(!err, "bad IR %04d op %d(%04d,%04d): %s",
95 i-REF_BIAS,
96 ir->o,
97 irm_op1(mode) == IRMref ? op1-REF_BIAS : op1,
98 irm_op2(mode) == IRMref ? op2-REF_BIAS : op2,
99 err);
100 }
101}
102
103/* Compare stack slots and frames of the recorder and the VM. */
104static void rec_check_slots(jit_State *J)
105{
106 BCReg s, nslots = J->baseslot + J->maxslot;
107 int32_t depth = 0;
108 cTValue *base = J->L->base - J->baseslot;
109 lj_assertJ(J->baseslot >= 1+LJ_FR2, "bad baseslot");
110 lj_assertJ(J->baseslot == 1+LJ_FR2 || (J->slot[J->baseslot-1] & TREF_FRAME),
111 "baseslot does not point to frame");
112 lj_assertJ(nslots <= LJ_MAX_JSLOTS, "slot overflow");
113 for (s = 0; s < nslots; s++) {
114 TRef tr = J->slot[s];
115 if (tr) {
116 cTValue *tv = &base[s];
117 IRRef ref = tref_ref(tr);
118 IRIns *ir = NULL; /* Silence compiler. */
119 if (!LJ_FR2 || ref || !(tr & (TREF_FRAME | TREF_CONT))) {
120 lj_assertJ(ref >= J->cur.nk && ref < J->cur.nins,
121 "slot %d ref %04d out of range", s, ref - REF_BIAS);
122 ir = IR(ref);
123 lj_assertJ(irt_t(ir->t) == tref_t(tr), "slot %d IR type mismatch", s);
124 }
125 if (s == 0) {
126 lj_assertJ(tref_isfunc(tr), "frame slot 0 is not a function");
127#if LJ_FR2
128 } else if (s == 1) {
129 lj_assertJ((tr & ~TREF_FRAME) == 0, "bad frame slot 1");
130#endif
131 } else if ((tr & TREF_FRAME)) {
132 GCfunc *fn = gco2func(frame_gc(tv));
133 BCReg delta = (BCReg)(tv - frame_prev(tv));
134#if LJ_FR2
135 lj_assertJ(!ref || ir_knum(ir)->u64 == tv->u64,
136 "frame slot %d PC mismatch", s);
137 tr = J->slot[s-1];
138 ir = IR(tref_ref(tr));
139#endif
140 lj_assertJ(tref_isfunc(tr),
141 "frame slot %d is not a function", s-LJ_FR2);
142 lj_assertJ(!tref_isk(tr) || fn == ir_kfunc(ir),
143 "frame slot %d function mismatch", s-LJ_FR2);
144 lj_assertJ(s > delta + LJ_FR2 ? (J->slot[s-delta] & TREF_FRAME)
145 : (s == delta + LJ_FR2),
146 "frame slot %d broken chain", s-LJ_FR2);
147 depth++;
148 } else if ((tr & TREF_CONT)) {
149#if LJ_FR2
150 lj_assertJ(!ref || ir_knum(ir)->u64 == tv->u64,
151 "cont slot %d continuation mismatch", s);
152#else
153 lj_assertJ(ir_kptr(ir) == gcrefp(tv->gcr, void),
154 "cont slot %d continuation mismatch", s);
155#endif
156 lj_assertJ((J->slot[s+1+LJ_FR2] & TREF_FRAME),
157 "cont slot %d not followed by frame", s);
158 depth++;
159 } else {
160 /* Number repr. may differ, but other types must be the same. */
161 lj_assertJ(tvisnumber(tv) ? tref_isnumber(tr) :
162 itype2irt(tv) == tref_type(tr),
163 "slot %d type mismatch: stack type %d vs IR type %d",
164 s, itypemap(tv), tref_type(tr));
165 if (tref_isk(tr)) { /* Compare constants. */
166 TValue tvk;
167 lj_ir_kvalue(J->L, &tvk, ir);
168 lj_assertJ((tvisnum(&tvk) && tvisnan(&tvk)) ?
169 (tvisnum(tv) && tvisnan(tv)) :
170 lj_obj_equal(tv, &tvk),
171 "slot %d const mismatch: stack %016llx vs IR %016llx",
172 s, tv->u64, tvk.u64);
173 }
174 }
175 }
176 }
177 lj_assertJ(J->framedepth == depth,
178 "frame depth mismatch %d vs %d", J->framedepth, depth);
179}
180#endif

182/* -- Type handling and specialization ------------------------------------ */
183
184/* Note: these functions return tagged references (TRef). */
185
186/* Specialize a slot to a specific type. Note: slot can be negative! */
187static TRef sloadt(jit_State *J, int32_t slot, IRType t, int mode)
188{
189 /* Caller may set IRT_GUARD in t. */
190 TRef ref = emitir_raw(IRT(IR_SLOAD, t), (int32_t)J->baseslot+slot, mode);
191 J->base[slot] = ref;
192 return ref;
193}
194
195/* Specialize a slot to the runtime type. Note: slot can be negative! */
196static TRef sload(jit_State *J, int32_t slot)
197{
198 IRType t = itype2irt(&J->L->base[slot]);
199 TRef ref = emitir_raw(IRTG(IR_SLOAD, t), (int32_t)J->baseslot+slot,
200 IRSLOAD_TYPECHECK);
201 if (irtype_ispri(t)) ref = TREF_PRI(t); /* Canonicalize primitive refs. */
202 J->base[slot] = ref;
203 return ref;
204}
205
206/* Get TRef from slot. Load slot and specialize if not done already. */
207#define getslot(J, s) (J->base[(s)] ? J->base[(s)] : sload(J, (int32_t)(s)))
208
209/* Get TRef for current function. */
210static TRef getcurrf(jit_State *J)
211{
212 if (J->base[-1-LJ_FR2])
213 return J->base[-1-LJ_FR2];
214 /* Non-base frame functions ought to be loaded already. */
215 lj_assertJ(J->baseslot == 1+LJ_FR2, "bad baseslot");
216 return sloadt(J, -1-LJ_FR2, IRT_FUNC, IRSLOAD_READONLY);
217}
218
219/* Compare for raw object equality.
220** Returns 0 if the objects are the same.
221** Returns 1 if they are different, but the same type.
222** Returns 2 for two different types.
223** Comparisons between primitives always return 1 -- no caller cares about it.
224*/
225int lj_record_objcmp(jit_State *J, TRef a, TRef b, cTValue *av, cTValue *bv)
226{
227 int diff = !lj_obj_equal(av, bv);
228 if (!tref_isk2(a, b)) { /* Shortcut, also handles primitives. */
229 IRType ta = tref_isinteger(a) ? IRT_INT : tref_type(a);
230 IRType tb = tref_isinteger(b) ? IRT_INT : tref_type(b);
231 if (ta != tb) {
232 /* Widen mixed number/int comparisons to number/number comparison. */
233 if (ta == IRT_INT && tb == IRT_NUM) {
234 a = emitir(IRTN(IR_CONV), a, IRCONV_NUM_INT);
235 ta = IRT_NUM;
236 } else if (ta == IRT_NUM && tb == IRT_INT) {
237 b = emitir(IRTN(IR_CONV), b, IRCONV_NUM_INT);
238 } else {
239 return 2; /* Two different types are never equal. */
240 }
241 }
242 emitir(IRTG(diff ? IR_NE : IR_EQ, ta), a, b);
243 }
244 return diff;
245}
246
247/* Constify a value. Returns 0 for non-representable object types. */
248TRef lj_record_constify(jit_State *J, cTValue *o)
249{
250 if (tvisgcv(o))
251 return lj_ir_kgc(J, gcV(o), itype2irt(o));
252 else if (tvisint(o))
253 return lj_ir_kint(J, intV(o));
254 else if (tvisnum(o))
255 return lj_ir_knumint(J, numV(o));
256 else if (tvisbool(o))
257 return TREF_PRI(itype2irt(o));
258 else
259 return 0; /* Can't represent lightuserdata (pointless). */
260}
261
262/* -- Record loop ops ----------------------------------------------------- */
263
264/* Loop event. */
265typedef enum {
266 LOOPEV_LEAVE, /* Loop is left or not entered. */
267 LOOPEV_ENTERLO, /* Loop is entered with a low iteration count left. */
268 LOOPEV_ENTER /* Loop is entered. */
269} LoopEvent;
270
271/* Canonicalize slots: convert integers to numbers. */
272static void canonicalize_slots(jit_State *J)
273{
274 BCReg s;
275 if (LJ_DUALNUM) return;
276 for (s = J->baseslot+J->maxslot-1; s >= 1; s--) {
277 TRef tr = J->slot[s];
278 if (tref_isinteger(tr)) {
279 IRIns *ir = IR(tref_ref(tr));
280 if (!(ir->o == IR_SLOAD && (ir->op2 & IRSLOAD_READONLY)))
281 J->slot[s] = emitir(IRTN(IR_CONV), tr, IRCONV_NUM_INT);
282 }
283 }
284}
285
286/* Stop recording. */
287void lj_record_stop(jit_State *J, TraceLink linktype, TraceNo lnk)
288{
289#ifdef LUAJIT_ENABLE_TABLE_BUMP
290 if (J->retryrec)
291 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_RETRY);
292#endif
293 lj_trace_end(J);
294 J->cur.linktype = (uint8_t)linktype;
295 J->cur.link = (uint16_t)lnk;
296 /* Looping back at the same stack level? */
297 if (lnk == J->cur.traceno && J->framedepth + J->retdepth == 0) {
298 if ((J->flags & JIT_F_OPT_LOOP)) /* Shall we try to create a loop? */
299 goto nocanon; /* Do not canonicalize or we lose the narrowing. */
300 if (J->cur.root) /* Otherwise ensure we always link to the root trace. */
301 J->cur.link = J->cur.root;
302 }
303 canonicalize_slots(J);
304nocanon:
305 /* Note: all loop ops must set J->pc to the following instruction! */
306 lj_snap_add(J); /* Add loop snapshot. */
307 J->needsnap = 0;
308 J->mergesnap = 1; /* In case recording continues. */
309}

311/* Search bytecode backwards for a int/num constant slot initializer. */
312static TRef find_kinit(jit_State *J, const BCIns *endpc, BCReg slot, IRType t)
313{
314 /* This algorithm is rather simplistic and assumes quite a bit about
315 ** how the bytecode is generated. It works fine for FORI initializers,
316 ** but it won't necessarily work in other cases (e.g. iterator arguments).
317 ** It doesn't do anything fancy, either (like backpropagating MOVs).
318 */
319 const BCIns *pc, *startpc = proto_bc(J->pt);
320 for (pc = endpc-1; pc > startpc; pc--) {
321 BCIns ins = *pc;
322 BCOp op = bc_op(ins);
323 /* First try to find the last instruction that stores to this slot. */
324 if (bcmode_a(op) == BCMbase && bc_a(ins) <= slot) {
325 return 0; /* Multiple results, e.g. from a CALL or KNIL. */
326 } else if (bcmode_a(op) == BCMdst && bc_a(ins) == slot) {
327 if (op == BC_KSHORT || op == BC_KNUM) { /* Found const. initializer. */
328 /* Now try to verify there's no forward jump across it. */
329 const BCIns *kpc = pc;
330 for (; pc > startpc; pc--)
331 if (bc_op(*pc) == BC_JMP) {
332 const BCIns *target = pc+bc_j(*pc)+1;
333 if (target > kpc && target <= endpc)
334 return 0; /* Conditional assignment. */
335 }
336 if (op == BC_KSHORT) {
337 int32_t k = (int32_t)(int16_t)bc_d(ins);
338 return t == IRT_INT ? lj_ir_kint(J, k) : lj_ir_knum(J, (lua_Number)k);
339 } else {
340 cTValue *tv = proto_knumtv(J->pt, bc_d(ins));
341 if (t == IRT_INT) {
342 int32_t k = numberVint(tv);
343 if (tvisint(tv) || numV(tv) == (lua_Number)k) /* -0 is ok here. */
344 return lj_ir_kint(J, k);
345 return 0; /* Type mismatch. */
346 } else {
347 return lj_ir_knum(J, numberVnum(tv));
348 }
349 }
350 }
351 return 0; /* Non-constant initializer. */
352 }
353 }
354 return 0; /* No assignment to this slot found? */
355}
356
357/* Load and optionally convert a FORI argument from a slot. */
358static TRef fori_load(jit_State *J, BCReg slot, IRType t, int mode)
359{
360 int conv = (tvisint(&J->L->base[slot]) != (t==IRT_INT)) ? IRSLOAD_CONVERT : 0;
361 return sloadt(J, (int32_t)slot,
362 t + (((mode & IRSLOAD_TYPECHECK) ||
363 (conv && t == IRT_INT && !(mode >> 16))) ?
364 IRT_GUARD : 0),
365 mode + conv);
366}
367
368/* Peek before FORI to find a const initializer. Otherwise load from slot. */
369static TRef fori_arg(jit_State *J, const BCIns *fori, BCReg slot,
370 IRType t, int mode)
371{
372 TRef tr = J->base[slot];
373 if (!tr) {
374 tr = find_kinit(J, fori, slot, t);
375 if (!tr)
376 tr = fori_load(J, slot, t, mode);
377 }
378 return tr;
379}

381/* Return the direction of the FOR loop iterator.
382** It's important to exactly reproduce the semantics of the interpreter.
383*/
384static int rec_for_direction(cTValue *o)
385{
386 return (tvisint(o) ? intV(o) : (int32_t)o->u32.hi) >= 0;
387}
388
389/* Simulate the runtime behavior of the FOR loop iterator. */
390static LoopEvent rec_for_iter(IROp *op, cTValue *o, int isforl)
391{
392 lua_Number stopv = numberVnum(&o[FORL_STOP]);
393 lua_Number idxv = numberVnum(&o[FORL_IDX]);
394 lua_Number stepv = numberVnum(&o[FORL_STEP]);
395 if (isforl)
396 idxv += stepv;
397 if (rec_for_direction(&o[FORL_STEP])) {
398 if (idxv <= stopv) {
399 *op = IR_LE;
400 return idxv + 2*stepv > stopv ? LOOPEV_ENTERLO : LOOPEV_ENTER;
401 }
402 *op = IR_GT; return LOOPEV_LEAVE;
403 } else {
404 if (stopv <= idxv) {
405 *op = IR_GE;
406 return idxv + 2*stepv < stopv ? LOOPEV_ENTERLO : LOOPEV_ENTER;
407 }
408 *op = IR_LT; return LOOPEV_LEAVE;
409 }
410}
411
412/* Record checks for FOR loop overflow and step direction. */
413static void rec_for_check(jit_State *J, IRType t, int dir,
414 TRef stop, TRef step, int init)
415{
416 if (!tref_isk(step)) {
417 /* Non-constant step: need a guard for the direction. */
418 TRef zero = (t == IRT_INT) ? lj_ir_kint(J, 0) : lj_ir_knum_zero(J);
419 emitir(IRTG(dir ? IR_GE : IR_LT, t), step, zero);
420 /* Add hoistable overflow checks for a narrowed FORL index. */
421 if (init && t == IRT_INT) {
422 if (tref_isk(stop)) {
423 /* Constant stop: optimize check away or to a range check for step. */
424 int32_t k = IR(tref_ref(stop))->i;
425 if (dir) {
426 if (k > 0)
427 emitir(IRTGI(IR_LE), step, lj_ir_kint(J, (int32_t)0x7fffffff-k));
428 } else {
429 if (k < 0)
430 emitir(IRTGI(IR_GE), step, lj_ir_kint(J, (int32_t)0x80000000-k));
431 }
432 } else {
433 /* Stop+step variable: need full overflow check. */
434 TRef tr = emitir(IRTGI(IR_ADDOV), step, stop);
435 emitir(IRTI(IR_USE), tr, 0); /* ADDOV is weak. Avoid dead result. */
436 }
437 }
438 } else if (init && t == IRT_INT && !tref_isk(stop)) {
439 /* Constant step: optimize overflow check to a range check for stop. */
440 int32_t k = IR(tref_ref(step))->i;
441 k = (int32_t)(dir ? 0x7fffffff : 0x80000000) - k;
442 emitir(IRTGI(dir ? IR_LE : IR_GE), stop, lj_ir_kint(J, k));
443 }
444}
445
446/* Record a FORL instruction. */
447static void rec_for_loop(jit_State *J, const BCIns *fori, ScEvEntry *scev,
448 int init)
449{
450 BCReg ra = bc_a(*fori);
451 cTValue *tv = &J->L->base[ra];
452 TRef idx = J->base[ra+FORL_IDX];
453 IRType t = idx ? tref_type(idx) :
454 (init || LJ_DUALNUM) ? lj_opt_narrow_forl(J, tv) : IRT_NUM;
455 int mode = IRSLOAD_INHERIT +
456 ((!LJ_DUALNUM || tvisint(tv) == (t == IRT_INT)) ? IRSLOAD_READONLY : 0);
457 TRef stop = fori_arg(J, fori, ra+FORL_STOP, t, mode);
458 TRef step = fori_arg(J, fori, ra+FORL_STEP, t, mode);
459 int tc, dir = rec_for_direction(&tv[FORL_STEP]);
460 lj_assertJ(bc_op(*fori) == BC_FORI || bc_op(*fori) == BC_JFORI,
461 "bad bytecode %d instead of FORI/JFORI", bc_op(*fori));
462 scev->t.irt = t;
463 scev->dir = dir;
464 scev->stop = tref_ref(stop);
465 scev->step = tref_ref(step);
466 rec_for_check(J, t, dir, stop, step, init);
467 scev->start = tref_ref(find_kinit(J, fori, ra+FORL_IDX, IRT_INT));
468 tc = (LJ_DUALNUM &&
469 !(scev->start && irref_isk(scev->stop) && irref_isk(scev->step) &&
470 tvisint(&tv[FORL_IDX]) == (t == IRT_INT))) ?
471 IRSLOAD_TYPECHECK : 0;
472 if (tc) {
473 J->base[ra+FORL_STOP] = stop;
474 J->base[ra+FORL_STEP] = step;
475 }
476 if (!idx)
477 idx = fori_load(J, ra+FORL_IDX, t,
478 IRSLOAD_INHERIT + tc + (J->scev.start << 16));
479 if (!init)
480 J->base[ra+FORL_IDX] = idx = emitir(IRT(IR_ADD, t), idx, step);
481 J->base[ra+FORL_EXT] = idx;
482 scev->idx = tref_ref(idx);
483 setmref(scev->pc, fori);
484 J->maxslot = ra+FORL_EXT+1;
485}
486
487/* Record FORL/JFORL or FORI/JFORI. */
488static LoopEvent rec_for(jit_State *J, const BCIns *fori, int isforl)
489{
490 BCReg ra = bc_a(*fori);
491 TValue *tv = &J->L->base[ra];
492 TRef *tr = &J->base[ra];
493 IROp op;
494 LoopEvent ev;
495 TRef stop;
496 IRType t;
497 if (isforl) { /* Handle FORL/JFORL opcodes. */
498 TRef idx = tr[FORL_IDX];
499 if (mref(J->scev.pc, const BCIns) == fori && tref_ref(idx) == J->scev.idx) {
500 t = J->scev.t.irt;
501 stop = J->scev.stop;
502 idx = emitir(IRT(IR_ADD, t), idx, J->scev.step);
503 tr[FORL_EXT] = tr[FORL_IDX] = idx;
504 } else {
505 ScEvEntry scev;
506 rec_for_loop(J, fori, &scev, 0);
507 t = scev.t.irt;
508 stop = scev.stop;
509 }
510 } else { /* Handle FORI/JFORI opcodes. */
511 BCReg i;
512 lj_meta_for(J->L, tv);
513 t = (LJ_DUALNUM || tref_isint(tr[FORL_IDX])) ? lj_opt_narrow_forl(J, tv) :
514 IRT_NUM;
515 for (i = FORL_IDX; i <= FORL_STEP; i++) {
516 if (!tr[i]) sload(J, ra+i);
517 lj_assertJ(tref_isnumber_str(tr[i]), "bad FORI argument type");
518 if (tref_isstr(tr[i]))
519 tr[i] = emitir(IRTG(IR_STRTO, IRT_NUM), tr[i], 0);
520 if (t == IRT_INT) {
521 if (!tref_isinteger(tr[i]))
522 tr[i] = emitir(IRTGI(IR_CONV), tr[i], IRCONV_INT_NUM|IRCONV_CHECK);
523 } else {
524 if (!tref_isnum(tr[i]))
525 tr[i] = emitir(IRTN(IR_CONV), tr[i], IRCONV_NUM_INT);
526 }
527 }
528 tr[FORL_EXT] = tr[FORL_IDX];
529 stop = tr[FORL_STOP];
530 rec_for_check(J, t, rec_for_direction(&tv[FORL_STEP]),
531 stop, tr[FORL_STEP], 1);
532 }
533
534 ev = rec_for_iter(&op, tv, isforl);
535 if (ev == LOOPEV_LEAVE) {
536 J->maxslot = ra+FORL_EXT+1;
537 J->pc = fori+1;
538 } else {
539 J->maxslot = ra;
540 J->pc = fori+bc_j(*fori)+1;
541 }
542 lj_snap_add(J);
543
544 emitir(IRTG(op, t), tr[FORL_IDX], stop);
545
546 if (ev == LOOPEV_LEAVE) {
547 J->maxslot = ra;
548 J->pc = fori+bc_j(*fori)+1;
549 } else {
550 J->maxslot = ra+FORL_EXT+1;
551 J->pc = fori+1;
552 }
553 J->needsnap = 1;
554 return ev;
555}
556
557/* Record ITERL/JITERL. */
558static LoopEvent rec_iterl(jit_State *J, const BCIns iterins)
559{
560 BCReg ra = bc_a(iterins);
561 if (!tref_isnil(getslot(J, ra))) { /* Looping back? */
562 J->base[ra-1] = J->base[ra]; /* Copy result of ITERC to control var. */
563 J->maxslot = ra-1+bc_b(J->pc[-1]);
564 J->pc += bc_j(iterins)+1;
565 return LOOPEV_ENTER;
566 } else {
567 J->maxslot = ra-3;
568 J->pc++;
569 return LOOPEV_LEAVE;
570 }
571}
572
573/* Record LOOP/JLOOP. Now, that was easy. */
574static LoopEvent rec_loop(jit_State *J, BCReg ra, int skip)
575{
576 if (ra < J->maxslot) J->maxslot = ra;
577 J->pc += skip;
578 return LOOPEV_ENTER;
579}
580
581/* Check if a loop repeatedly failed to trace because it didn't loop back. */
582static int innerloopleft(jit_State *J, const BCIns *pc)
583{
584 ptrdiff_t i;
585 for (i = 0; i < PENALTY_SLOTS; i++)
586 if (mref(J->penalty[i].pc, const BCIns) == pc) {
587 if ((J->penalty[i].reason == LJ_TRERR_LLEAVE ||
588 J->penalty[i].reason == LJ_TRERR_LINNER) &&
589 J->penalty[i].val >= 2*PENALTY_MIN)
590 return 1;
591 break;
592 }
593 return 0;
594}
595
596/* Handle the case when an interpreted loop op is hit. */
597static void rec_loop_interp(jit_State *J, const BCIns *pc, LoopEvent ev)
598{
599 if (J->parent == 0 && J->exitno == 0) {
600 if (pc == J->startpc && J->framedepth + J->retdepth == 0) {
601 /* Same loop? */
602 if (ev == LOOPEV_LEAVE) /* Must loop back to form a root trace. */
603 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_LLEAVE);
604 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_LOOP, J->cur.traceno); /* Looping trace. */
605 } else if (ev != LOOPEV_LEAVE) { /* Entering inner loop? */
606 /* It's usually better to abort here and wait until the inner loop
607 ** is traced. But if the inner loop repeatedly didn't loop back,
608 ** this indicates a low trip count. In this case try unrolling
609 ** an inner loop even in a root trace. But it's better to be a bit
610 ** more conservative here and only do it for very short loops.
611 */
612 if (bc_j(*pc) != -1 && !innerloopleft(J, pc))
613 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_LINNER); /* Root trace hit an inner loop. */
614 if ((ev != LOOPEV_ENTERLO &&
615 J->loopref && J->cur.nins - J->loopref > 24) || --J->loopunroll < 0)
616 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_LUNROLL); /* Limit loop unrolling. */
617 J->loopref = J->cur.nins;
618 }
619 } else if (ev != LOOPEV_LEAVE) { /* Side trace enters an inner loop. */
620 J->loopref = J->cur.nins;
621 if (--J->loopunroll < 0)
622 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_LUNROLL); /* Limit loop unrolling. */
623 } /* Side trace continues across a loop that's left or not entered. */
624}
625
626/* Handle the case when an already compiled loop op is hit. */
627static void rec_loop_jit(jit_State *J, TraceNo lnk, LoopEvent ev)
628{
629 if (J->parent == 0 && J->exitno == 0) { /* Root trace hit an inner loop. */
630 /* Better let the inner loop spawn a side trace back here. */
631 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_LINNER);
632 } else if (ev != LOOPEV_LEAVE) { /* Side trace enters a compiled loop. */
633 J->instunroll = 0; /* Cannot continue across a compiled loop op. */
634 if (J->pc == J->startpc && J->framedepth + J->retdepth == 0)
635 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_LOOP, J->cur.traceno); /* Form extra loop. */
636 else
637 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_ROOT, lnk); /* Link to the loop. */
638 } /* Side trace continues across a loop that's left or not entered. */
639}

646static int rec_profile_need(jit_State *J, GCproto *pt, const BCIns *pc)
647{

688/* -- Record calls and returns -------------------------------------------- */
689
690/* Specialize to the runtime value of the called function or its prototype. */
691static TRef rec_call_specialize(jit_State *J, GCfunc *fn, TRef tr)
692{
693 TRef kfunc;
694 if (isluafunc(fn)) {
695 GCproto *pt = funcproto(fn);
696 /* Too many closures created? Probably not a monomorphic function. */
697 if (pt->flags >= PROTO_CLC_POLY) { /* Specialize to prototype instead. */
698 TRef trpt = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_PGC), tr, IRFL_FUNC_PC);
699 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_PGC), trpt, lj_ir_kptr(J, proto_bc(pt)));
700 (void)lj_ir_kgc(J, obj2gco(pt), IRT_PROTO); /* Prevent GC of proto. */
701 return tr;
702 }
703 } else {
704 /* Don't specialize to non-monomorphic builtins. */
705 switch (fn->c.ffid) {
706 case FF_coroutine_wrap_aux:
707 case FF_string_gmatch_aux:
708 /* NYI: io_file_iter doesn't have an ffid, yet. */
709 { /* Specialize to the ffid. */
710 TRef trid = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_U8), tr, IRFL_FUNC_FFID);
711 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_INT), trid, lj_ir_kint(J, fn->c.ffid));
712 }
713 return tr;
714 default:
715 /* NYI: don't specialize to non-monomorphic C functions. */
716 break;
717 }
718 }
719 /* Otherwise specialize to the function (closure) value itself. */
720 kfunc = lj_ir_kfunc(J, fn);
721 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_FUNC), tr, kfunc);
722 return kfunc;
723}
724
725/* Record call setup. */
726static void rec_call_setup(jit_State *J, BCReg func, ptrdiff_t nargs)
727{
728 RecordIndex ix;
729 TValue *functv = &J->L->base[func];
730 TRef kfunc, *fbase = &J->base[func];
731 ptrdiff_t i;
732 (void)getslot(J, func); /* Ensure func has a reference. */
733 for (i = 1; i <= nargs; i++)
734 (void)getslot(J, func+LJ_FR2+i); /* Ensure all args have a reference. */
735 if (!tref_isfunc(fbase[0])) { /* Resolve __call metamethod. */
736 ix.tab = fbase[0];
737 copyTV(J->L, &ix.tabv, functv);
738 if (!lj_record_mm_lookup(J, &ix, MM_call) || !tref_isfunc(ix.mobj))
739 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NOMM);
740 for (i = ++nargs; i > LJ_FR2; i--) /* Shift arguments up. */
741 fbase[i+LJ_FR2] = fbase[i+LJ_FR2-1];
742#if LJ_FR2
743 fbase[2] = fbase[0];
744#endif
745 fbase[0] = ix.mobj; /* Replace function. */
746 functv = &ix.mobjv;
747 }
748 kfunc = rec_call_specialize(J, funcV(functv), fbase[0]);
749#if LJ_FR2
750 fbase[0] = kfunc;
751 fbase[1] = TREF_FRAME;
752#else
753 fbase[0] = kfunc | TREF_FRAME;
754#endif
755 J->maxslot = (BCReg)nargs;
756}
757
758/* Record call. */
759void lj_record_call(jit_State *J, BCReg func, ptrdiff_t nargs)
760{
761 rec_call_setup(J, func, nargs);
762 /* Bump frame. */
763 J->framedepth++;
764 J->base += func+1+LJ_FR2;
765 J->baseslot += func+1+LJ_FR2;
766 if (J->baseslot + J->maxslot >= LJ_MAX_JSLOTS)
767 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_STACKOV);
768}
769
770/* Record tail call. */
771void lj_record_tailcall(jit_State *J, BCReg func, ptrdiff_t nargs)
772{
773 rec_call_setup(J, func, nargs);
774 if (frame_isvarg(J->L->base - 1)) {
775 BCReg cbase = (BCReg)frame_delta(J->L->base - 1);
776 if (--J->framedepth < 0)
777 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NYIRETL);
778 J->baseslot -= (BCReg)cbase;
779 J->base -= cbase;
780 func += cbase;
781 }
782 /* Move func + args down. */
783 if (LJ_FR2 && J->baseslot == 2)
784 J->base[func+1] = TREF_FRAME;
785 memmove(&J->base[-1-LJ_FR2], &J->base[func], sizeof(TRef)*(J->maxslot+1+LJ_FR2));
786 /* Note: the new TREF_FRAME is now at J->base[-1] (even for slot #0). */
787 /* Tailcalls can form a loop, so count towards the loop unroll limit. */
788 if (++J->tailcalled > J->loopunroll)
789 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_LUNROLL);
790}
791
792/* Check unroll limits for down-recursion. */
793static int check_downrec_unroll(jit_State *J, GCproto *pt)
794{
795 IRRef ptref;
796 for (ptref = J->chain[IR_KGC]; ptref; ptref = IR(ptref)->prev)
797 if (ir_kgc(IR(ptref)) == obj2gco(pt)) {
798 int count = 0;
799 IRRef ref;
800 for (ref = J->chain[IR_RETF]; ref; ref = IR(ref)->prev)
801 if (IR(ref)->op1 == ptref)
802 count++;
803 if (count) {
804 if (J->pc == J->startpc) {
805 if (count + J->tailcalled > J->param[JIT_P_recunroll])
806 return 1;
807 } else {
808 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_DOWNREC);
809 }
810 }
811 }
812 return 0;
813}
814
815static TRef rec_cat(jit_State *J, BCReg baseslot, BCReg topslot);
816
817/* Record return. */
818void lj_record_ret(jit_State *J, BCReg rbase, ptrdiff_t gotresults)
819{
820 TValue *frame = J->L->base - 1;
821 ptrdiff_t i;
822 for (i = 0; i < gotresults; i++)
823 (void)getslot(J, rbase+i); /* Ensure all results have a reference. */
824 while (frame_ispcall(frame)) { /* Immediately resolve pcall() returns. */
825 BCReg cbase = (BCReg)frame_delta(frame);
826 if (--J->framedepth <= 0)
827 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NYIRETL);
828 lj_assertJ(J->baseslot > 1+LJ_FR2, "bad baseslot for return");
829 gotresults++;
830 rbase += cbase;
831 J->baseslot -= (BCReg)cbase;
832 J->base -= cbase;
833 J->base[--rbase] = TREF_TRUE; /* Prepend true to results. */
834 frame = frame_prevd(frame);
835 J->needsnap = 1; /* Stop catching on-trace errors. */
836 }
837 /* Return to lower frame via interpreter for unhandled cases. */
838 if (J->framedepth == 0 && J->pt && bc_isret(bc_op(*J->pc)) &&
839 (!frame_islua(frame) ||
840 (J->parent == 0 && J->exitno == 0 &&
841 !bc_isret(bc_op(J->cur.startins))))) {
842 /* NYI: specialize to frame type and return directly, not via RET*. */
843 for (i = 0; i < (ptrdiff_t)rbase; i++)
844 J->base[i] = 0; /* Purge dead slots. */
845 J->maxslot = rbase + (BCReg)gotresults;
846 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_RETURN, 0); /* Return to interpreter. */
847 return;
848 }
849 if (frame_isvarg(frame)) {
850 BCReg cbase = (BCReg)frame_delta(frame);
851 if (--J->framedepth < 0) /* NYI: return of vararg func to lower frame. */
852 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NYIRETL);
853 lj_assertJ(J->baseslot > 1+LJ_FR2, "bad baseslot for return");
854 rbase += cbase;
855 J->baseslot -= (BCReg)cbase;
856 J->base -= cbase;
857 frame = frame_prevd(frame);
858 }
859 if (frame_islua(frame)) { /* Return to Lua frame. */
860 BCIns callins = *(frame_pc(frame)-1);
861 ptrdiff_t nresults = bc_b(callins) ? (ptrdiff_t)bc_b(callins)-1 :gotresults;
862 BCReg cbase = bc_a(callins);
863 GCproto *pt = funcproto(frame_func(frame - (cbase+1+LJ_FR2)));
864 if ((pt->flags & PROTO_NOJIT))
865 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_CJITOFF);
866 if (J->framedepth == 0 && J->pt && frame == J->L->base - 1) {
867 if (check_downrec_unroll(J, pt)) {
868 J->maxslot = (BCReg)(rbase + gotresults);
869 lj_snap_purge(J);
870 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_DOWNREC, J->cur.traceno); /* Down-rec. */
871 return;
872 }
873 lj_snap_add(J);
874 }
875 for (i = 0; i < nresults; i++) /* Adjust results. */
876 J->base[i-1-LJ_FR2] = i < gotresults ? J->base[rbase+i] : TREF_NIL;
877 J->maxslot = cbase+(BCReg)nresults;
878 if (J->framedepth > 0) { /* Return to a frame that is part of the trace. */
879 J->framedepth--;
880 lj_assertJ(J->baseslot > cbase+1+LJ_FR2, "bad baseslot for return");
881 J->baseslot -= cbase+1+LJ_FR2;
882 J->base -= cbase+1+LJ_FR2;
883 } else if (J->parent == 0 && J->exitno == 0 &&
884 !bc_isret(bc_op(J->cur.startins))) {
885 /* Return to lower frame would leave the loop in a root trace. */
886 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_LLEAVE);
887 } else if (J->needsnap) { /* Tailcalled to ff with side-effects. */
888 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NYIRETL); /* No way to insert snapshot here. */
889 } else { /* Return to lower frame. Guard for the target we return to. */
890 TRef trpt = lj_ir_kgc(J, obj2gco(pt), IRT_PROTO);
891 TRef trpc = lj_ir_kptr(J, (void *)frame_pc(frame));
892 emitir(IRTG(IR_RETF, IRT_PGC), trpt, trpc);
893 J->retdepth++;
894 J->needsnap = 1;
895 lj_assertJ(J->baseslot == 1+LJ_FR2, "bad baseslot for return");
896 /* Shift result slots up and clear the slots of the new frame below. */
897 memmove(J->base + cbase, J->base-1-LJ_FR2, sizeof(TRef)*nresults);
898 memset(J->base-1-LJ_FR2, 0, sizeof(TRef)*(cbase+1+LJ_FR2));
899 }
900 } else if (frame_iscont(frame)) { /* Return to continuation frame. */
901 ASMFunction cont = frame_contf(frame);
902 BCReg cbase = (BCReg)frame_delta(frame);
903 if ((J->framedepth -= 2) < 0)
904 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NYIRETL);
905 J->baseslot -= (BCReg)cbase;
906 J->base -= cbase;
907 J->maxslot = cbase-(2<<LJ_FR2);
908 if (cont == lj_cont_ra) {
909 /* Copy result to destination slot. */
910 BCReg dst = bc_a(*(frame_contpc(frame)-1));
911 J->base[dst] = gotresults ? J->base[cbase+rbase] : TREF_NIL;
912 if (dst >= J->maxslot) {
913 J->maxslot = dst+1;
914 }
915 } else if (cont == lj_cont_nop) {
916 /* Nothing to do here. */
917 } else if (cont == lj_cont_cat) {
918 BCReg bslot = bc_b(*(frame_contpc(frame)-1));
919 TRef tr = gotresults ? J->base[cbase+rbase] : TREF_NIL;
920 if (bslot != J->maxslot) { /* Concatenate the remainder. */
921 TValue *b = J->L->base, save; /* Simulate lower frame and result. */
922 /* Can't handle MM_concat + CALLT + fast func side-effects. */
923 if (J->postproc != LJ_POST_NONE)
924 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NYIRETL);
925 J->base[J->maxslot] = tr;
926 copyTV(J->L, &save, b-(2<<LJ_FR2));
927 if (gotresults)
928 copyTV(J->L, b-(2<<LJ_FR2), b+rbase);
929 else
930 setnilV(b-(2<<LJ_FR2));
931 J->L->base = b - cbase;
932 tr = rec_cat(J, bslot, cbase-(2<<LJ_FR2));
933 b = J->L->base + cbase; /* Undo. */
934 J->L->base = b;
935 copyTV(J->L, b-(2<<LJ_FR2), &save);
936 }
937 if (tr) { /* Store final result. */
938 BCReg dst = bc_a(*(frame_contpc(frame)-1));
939 J->base[dst] = tr;
940 if (dst >= J->maxslot) {
941 J->maxslot = dst+1;
942 }
943 } /* Otherwise continue with another __concat call. */
944 } else {
945 /* Result type already specialized. */
946 lj_assertJ(cont == lj_cont_condf || cont == lj_cont_condt,
947 "bad continuation type");
948 }
949 } else {
950 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NYIRETL); /* NYI: handle return to C frame. */
951 }
952 lj_assertJ(J->baseslot >= 1+LJ_FR2, "bad baseslot for return");
953}

955/* -- Metamethod handling ------------------------------------------------- */
956
957/* Prepare to record call to metamethod. */
958static BCReg rec_mm_prep(jit_State *J, ASMFunction cont)
959{
960 BCReg s, top = cont == lj_cont_cat ? J->maxslot : curr_proto(J->L)->framesize;
961#if LJ_FR2
962 J->base[top] = lj_ir_k64(J, IR_KNUM, u64ptr(contptr(cont)));
963 J->base[top+1] = TREF_CONT;
964#else
965 J->base[top] = lj_ir_kptr(J, contptr(cont)) | TREF_CONT;
966#endif
967 J->framedepth++;
968 for (s = J->maxslot; s < top; s++)
969 J->base[s] = 0; /* Clear frame gap to avoid resurrecting previous refs. */
970 return top+1+LJ_FR2;
971}
972
973/* Record metamethod lookup. */
974int lj_record_mm_lookup(jit_State *J, RecordIndex *ix, MMS mm)
975{
976 RecordIndex mix;
977 GCtab *mt;
978 if (tref_istab(ix->tab)) {
979 mt = tabref(tabV(&ix->tabv)->metatable);
980 mix.tab = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_TAB), ix->tab, IRFL_TAB_META);
981 } else if (tref_isudata(ix->tab)) {
982 int udtype = udataV(&ix->tabv)->udtype;
983 mt = tabref(udataV(&ix->tabv)->metatable);
984 /* The metatables of special userdata objects are treated as immutable. */
985 if (udtype != UDTYPE_USERDATA) {
986 cTValue *mo;
987 if (LJ_HASFFI && udtype == UDTYPE_FFI_CLIB) {
988 /* Specialize to the C library namespace object. */
989 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_PGC), ix->tab, lj_ir_kptr(J, udataV(&ix->tabv)));
990 } else {
991 /* Specialize to the type of userdata. */
992 TRef tr = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_U8), ix->tab, IRFL_UDATA_UDTYPE);
993 emitir(IRTGI(IR_EQ), tr, lj_ir_kint(J, udtype));
994 }
995 immutable_mt:
996 mo = lj_tab_getstr(mt, mmname_str(J2G(J), mm));
997 if (!mo || tvisnil(mo))
998 return 0; /* No metamethod. */
999 /* Treat metamethod or index table as immutable, too. */
1000 if (!(tvisfunc(mo) || tvistab(mo)))
1001 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_BADTYPE);
1002 copyTV(J->L, &ix->mobjv, mo);
1003 ix->mobj = lj_ir_kgc(J, gcV(mo), tvisfunc(mo) ? IRT_FUNC : IRT_TAB);
1004 ix->mtv = mt;
1005 ix->mt = TREF_NIL; /* Dummy value for comparison semantics. */
1006 return 1; /* Got metamethod or index table. */
1007 }
1008 mix.tab = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_TAB), ix->tab, IRFL_UDATA_META);
1009 } else {
1010 /* Specialize to base metatable. Must flush mcode in lua_setmetatable(). */
1011 mt = tabref(basemt_obj(J2G(J), &ix->tabv));
1012 if (mt == NULL) {
1013 ix->mt = TREF_NIL;
1014 return 0; /* No metamethod. */
1015 }
1016 /* The cdata metatable is treated as immutable. */
1017 if (LJ_HASFFI && tref_iscdata(ix->tab)) goto immutable_mt;
1018 ix->mt = mix.tab = lj_ir_ggfload(J, IRT_TAB,
1019 GG_OFS(g.gcroot[GCROOT_BASEMT+itypemap(&ix->tabv)]));
1020 goto nocheck;
1021 }
1022 ix->mt = mt ? mix.tab : TREF_NIL;
1023 emitir(IRTG(mt ? IR_NE : IR_EQ, IRT_TAB), mix.tab, lj_ir_knull(J, IRT_TAB));
1024nocheck:
1025 if (mt) {
1026 GCstr *mmstr = mmname_str(J2G(J), mm);
1027 cTValue *mo = lj_tab_getstr(mt, mmstr);
1028 if (mo && !tvisnil(mo))
1029 copyTV(J->L, &ix->mobjv, mo);
1030 ix->mtv = mt;
1031 settabV(J->L, &mix.tabv, mt);
1032 setstrV(J->L, &mix.keyv, mmstr);
1033 mix.key = lj_ir_kstr(J, mmstr);
1034 mix.val = 0;
1035 mix.idxchain = 0;
1036 ix->mobj = lj_record_idx(J, &mix);
1037 return !tref_isnil(ix->mobj); /* 1 if metamethod found, 0 if not. */
1038 }
1039 return 0; /* No metamethod. */
1040}
1041
1042/* Record call to arithmetic metamethod. */
1043static TRef rec_mm_arith(jit_State *J, RecordIndex *ix, MMS mm)
1044{
1045 /* Set up metamethod call first to save ix->tab and ix->tabv. */
1046 BCReg func = rec_mm_prep(J, mm == MM_concat ? lj_cont_cat : lj_cont_ra);
1047 TRef *base = J->base + func;
1048 TValue *basev = J->L->base + func;
1049 base[1+LJ_FR2] = ix->tab; base[2+LJ_FR2] = ix->key;
1050 copyTV(J->L, basev+1+LJ_FR2, &ix->tabv);
1051 copyTV(J->L, basev+2+LJ_FR2, &ix->keyv);
1052 if (!lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, mm)) { /* Lookup mm on 1st operand. */
1053 if (mm != MM_unm) {
1054 ix->tab = ix->key;
1055 copyTV(J->L, &ix->tabv, &ix->keyv);
1056 if (lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, mm)) /* Lookup mm on 2nd operand. */
1057 goto ok;
1058 }
1059 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NOMM);
1060 }
1061ok:
1062 base[0] = ix->mobj;
1063#if LJ_FR2
1064 base[1] = 0;
1065#endif
1066 copyTV(J->L, basev+0, &ix->mobjv);
1067 lj_record_call(J, func, 2);
1068 return 0; /* No result yet. */
1069}
1070
1071/* Record call to __len metamethod. */
1072static TRef rec_mm_len(jit_State *J, TRef tr, TValue *tv)
1073{
1074 RecordIndex ix;
1075 ix.tab = tr;
1076 copyTV(J->L, &ix.tabv, tv);
1077 if (lj_record_mm_lookup(J, &ix, MM_len)) {
1078 BCReg func = rec_mm_prep(J, lj_cont_ra);
1079 TRef *base = J->base + func;
1080 TValue *basev = J->L->base + func;
1081 base[0] = ix.mobj; copyTV(J->L, basev+0, &ix.mobjv);
1082 base += LJ_FR2;
1083 basev += LJ_FR2;
1084 base[1] = tr; copyTV(J->L, basev+1, tv);
1085#if LJ_52
1086 base[2] = tr; copyTV(J->L, basev+2, tv);
1087#else
1088 base[2] = TREF_NIL; setnilV(basev+2);
1089#endif
1090 lj_record_call(J, func, 2);
1091 } else {
1092 if (LJ_52 && tref_istab(tr))
1093 return emitir(IRTI(IR_ALEN), tr, TREF_NIL);
1094 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NOMM);
1095 }
1096 return 0; /* No result yet. */
1097}
1098
1099/* Call a comparison metamethod. */
1100static void rec_mm_callcomp(jit_State *J, RecordIndex *ix, int op)
1101{
1102 BCReg func = rec_mm_prep(J, (op&1) ? lj_cont_condf : lj_cont_condt);
1103 TRef *base = J->base + func + LJ_FR2;
1104 TValue *tv = J->L->base + func + LJ_FR2;
1105 base[-LJ_FR2] = ix->mobj; base[1] = ix->val; base[2] = ix->key;
1106 copyTV(J->L, tv-LJ_FR2, &ix->mobjv);
1107 copyTV(J->L, tv+1, &ix->valv);
1108 copyTV(J->L, tv+2, &ix->keyv);
1109 lj_record_call(J, func, 2);
1110}
1111
1112/* Record call to equality comparison metamethod (for tab and udata only). */
1113static void rec_mm_equal(jit_State *J, RecordIndex *ix, int op)
1114{
1115 ix->tab = ix->val;
1116 copyTV(J->L, &ix->tabv, &ix->valv);
1117 if (lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, MM_eq)) { /* Lookup mm on 1st operand. */
1118 cTValue *bv;
1119 TRef mo1 = ix->mobj;
1120 TValue mo1v;
1121 copyTV(J->L, &mo1v, &ix->mobjv);
1122 /* Avoid the 2nd lookup and the objcmp if the metatables are equal. */
1123 bv = &ix->keyv;
1124 if (tvistab(bv) && tabref(tabV(bv)->metatable) == ix->mtv) {
1125 TRef mt2 = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_TAB), ix->key, IRFL_TAB_META);
1126 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_TAB), mt2, ix->mt);
1127 } else if (tvisudata(bv) && tabref(udataV(bv)->metatable) == ix->mtv) {
1128 TRef mt2 = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_TAB), ix->key, IRFL_UDATA_META);
1129 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_TAB), mt2, ix->mt);
1130 } else { /* Lookup metamethod on 2nd operand and compare both. */
1131 ix->tab = ix->key;
1132 copyTV(J->L, &ix->tabv, bv);
1133 if (!lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, MM_eq) ||
1134 lj_record_objcmp(J, mo1, ix->mobj, &mo1v, &ix->mobjv))
1135 return;
1136 }
1137 rec_mm_callcomp(J, ix, op);
1138 }
1139}
1140
1141/* Record call to ordered comparison metamethods (for arbitrary objects). */
1142static void rec_mm_comp(jit_State *J, RecordIndex *ix, int op)
1143{
1144 ix->tab = ix->val;
1145 copyTV(J->L, &ix->tabv, &ix->valv);
1146 while (1) {
1147 MMS mm = (op & 2) ? MM_le : MM_lt; /* Try __le + __lt or only __lt. */
1148#if LJ_52
1149 if (!lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, mm)) { /* Lookup mm on 1st operand. */
1150 ix->tab = ix->key;
1151 copyTV(J->L, &ix->tabv, &ix->keyv);
1152 if (!lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, mm)) /* Lookup mm on 2nd operand. */
1153 goto nomatch;
1154 }
1155 rec_mm_callcomp(J, ix, op);
1156 return;
1157#else
1158 if (lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, mm)) { /* Lookup mm on 1st operand. */
1159 cTValue *bv;
1160 TRef mo1 = ix->mobj;
1161 TValue mo1v;
1162 copyTV(J->L, &mo1v, &ix->mobjv);
1163 /* Avoid the 2nd lookup and the objcmp if the metatables are equal. */
1164 bv = &ix->keyv;
1165 if (tvistab(bv) && tabref(tabV(bv)->metatable) == ix->mtv) {
1166 TRef mt2 = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_TAB), ix->key, IRFL_TAB_META);
1167 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_TAB), mt2, ix->mt);
1168 } else if (tvisudata(bv) && tabref(udataV(bv)->metatable) == ix->mtv) {
1169 TRef mt2 = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_TAB), ix->key, IRFL_UDATA_META);
1170 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_TAB), mt2, ix->mt);
1171 } else { /* Lookup metamethod on 2nd operand and compare both. */
1172 ix->tab = ix->key;
1173 copyTV(J->L, &ix->tabv, bv);
1174 if (!lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, mm) ||
1175 lj_record_objcmp(J, mo1, ix->mobj, &mo1v, &ix->mobjv))
1176 goto nomatch;
1177 }
1178 rec_mm_callcomp(J, ix, op);
1179 return;
1180 }
1181#endif
1182 nomatch:
1183 /* Lookup failed. Retry with __lt and swapped operands. */
1184 if (!(op & 2)) break; /* Already at __lt. Interpreter will throw. */
1185 ix->tab = ix->key; ix->key = ix->val; ix->val = ix->tab;
1186 copyTV(J->L, &ix->tabv, &ix->keyv);
1187 copyTV(J->L, &ix->keyv, &ix->valv);
1188 copyTV(J->L, &ix->valv, &ix->tabv);
1189 op ^= 3;
1190 }
1191}
1192
1193#if LJ_HASFFI
1194/* Setup call to cdata comparison metamethod. */
1195static void rec_mm_comp_cdata(jit_State *J, RecordIndex *ix, int op, MMS mm)
1196{
1197 lj_snap_add(J);
1198 if (tref_iscdata(ix->val)) {
1199 ix->tab = ix->val;
1200 copyTV(J->L, &ix->tabv, &ix->valv);
1201 } else {
1202 lj_assertJ(tref_iscdata(ix->key), "cdata expected");
1203 ix->tab = ix->key;
1204 copyTV(J->L, &ix->tabv, &ix->keyv);
1205 }
1206 lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, mm);
1207 rec_mm_callcomp(J, ix, op);
1208}

1213#ifdef LUAJIT_ENABLE_TABLE_BUMP
1214/* Bump table allocations in bytecode when they grow during recording. */
1215static void rec_idx_bump(jit_State *J, RecordIndex *ix)
1216{
1217 RBCHashEntry *rbc = &J->rbchash[(ix->tab & (RBCHASH_SLOTS-1))];
1218 if (tref_ref(ix->tab) == rbc->ref) {
1219 const BCIns *pc = mref(rbc->pc, const BCIns);
1220 GCtab *tb = tabV(&ix->tabv);
1221 uint32_t nhbits;
1222 IRIns *ir;
1223 if (!tvisnil(&ix->keyv))
1224 (void)lj_tab_set(J->L, tb, &ix->keyv); /* Grow table right now. */
1225 nhbits = tb->hmask > 0 ? lj_fls(tb->hmask)+1 : 0;
1226 ir = IR(tref_ref(ix->tab));
1227 if (ir->o == IR_TNEW) {
1228 uint32_t ah = bc_d(*pc);
1229 uint32_t asize = ah & 0x7ff, hbits = ah >> 11;
1230 if (nhbits > hbits) hbits = nhbits;
1231 if (tb->asize > asize) {
1232 asize = tb->asize <= 0x7ff ? tb->asize : 0x7ff;
1233 }
1234 if ((asize | (hbits<<11)) != ah) { /* Has the size changed? */
1235 /* Patch bytecode, but continue recording (for more patching). */
1236 setbc_d(pc, (asize | (hbits<<11)));
1237 /* Patching TNEW operands is only safe if the trace is aborted. */
1238 ir->op1 = asize; ir->op2 = hbits;
1239 J->retryrec = 1; /* Abort the trace at the end of recording. */
1240 }
1241 } else if (ir->o == IR_TDUP) {
1242 GCtab *tpl = gco2tab(proto_kgc(&gcref(rbc->pt)->pt, ~(ptrdiff_t)bc_d(*pc)));
1243 /* Grow template table, but preserve keys with nil values. */
1244 if ((tb->asize > tpl->asize && (1u << nhbits)-1 == tpl->hmask) ||
1245 (tb->asize == tpl->asize && (1u << nhbits)-1 > tpl->hmask)) {
1246 Node *node = noderef(tpl->node);
1247 uint32_t i, hmask = tpl->hmask, asize;
1248 TValue *array;
1249 for (i = 0; i <= hmask; i++) {
1250 if (!tvisnil(&node[i].key) && tvisnil(&node[i].val))
1251 settabV(J->L, &node[i].val, tpl);
1252 }
1253 if (!tvisnil(&ix->keyv) && tref_isk(ix->key)) {
1254 TValue *o = lj_tab_set(J->L, tpl, &ix->keyv);
1255 if (tvisnil(o)) settabV(J->L, o, tpl);
1256 }
1257 lj_tab_resize(J->L, tpl, tb->asize, nhbits);
1258 node = noderef(tpl->node);
1259 hmask = tpl->hmask;
1260 for (i = 0; i <= hmask; i++) {
1261 /* This is safe, since template tables only hold immutable values. */
1262 if (tvistab(&node[i].val))
1263 setnilV(&node[i].val);
1264 }
1265 /* The shape of the table may have changed. Clean up array part, too. */
1266 asize = tpl->asize;
1267 array = tvref(tpl->array);
1268 for (i = 0; i < asize; i++) {
1269 if (tvistab(&array[i]))
1270 setnilV(&array[i]);
1271 }
1272 J->retryrec = 1; /* Abort the trace at the end of recording. */
1273 }
1274 }
1275 }
1276}
1277#endif
1278
1279/* Record bounds-check. */
1280static void rec_idx_abc(jit_State *J, TRef asizeref, TRef ikey, uint32_t asize)
1281{
1282 /* Try to emit invariant bounds checks. */
1283 if ((J->flags & (JIT_F_OPT_LOOP|JIT_F_OPT_ABC)) ==
1284 (JIT_F_OPT_LOOP|JIT_F_OPT_ABC)) {
1285 IRRef ref = tref_ref(ikey);
1286 IRIns *ir = IR(ref);
1287 int32_t ofs = 0;
1288 IRRef ofsref = 0;
1289 /* Handle constant offsets. */
1290 if (ir->o == IR_ADD && irref_isk(ir->op2)) {
1291 ofsref = ir->op2;
1292 ofs = IR(ofsref)->i;
1293 ref = ir->op1;
1294 ir = IR(ref);
1295 }
1296 /* Got scalar evolution analysis results for this reference? */
1297 if (ref == J->scev.idx) {
1298 int32_t stop;
1299 lj_assertJ(irt_isint(J->scev.t) && ir->o == IR_SLOAD,
1300 "only int SCEV supported");
1301 stop = numberVint(&(J->L->base - J->baseslot)[ir->op1 + FORL_STOP]);
1302 /* Runtime value for stop of loop is within bounds? */
1303 if ((uint64_t)stop + ofs < (uint64_t)asize) {
1304 /* Emit invariant bounds check for stop. */
1305 emitir(IRTG(IR_ABC, IRT_P32), asizeref, ofs == 0 ? J->scev.stop :
1306 emitir(IRTI(IR_ADD), J->scev.stop, ofsref));
1307 /* Emit invariant bounds check for start, if not const or negative. */
1308 if (!(J->scev.dir && J->scev.start &&
1309 (int64_t)IR(J->scev.start)->i + ofs >= 0))
1310 emitir(IRTG(IR_ABC, IRT_P32), asizeref, ikey);
1311 return;
1312 }
1313 }
1314 }
1315 emitir(IRTGI(IR_ABC), asizeref, ikey); /* Emit regular bounds check. */
1316}
1317
1318/* Record indexed key lookup. */
1319static TRef rec_idx_key(jit_State *J, RecordIndex *ix, IRRef *rbref,
1320 IRType1 *rbguard)
1321{
1322 TRef key;
1323 GCtab *t = tabV(&ix->tabv);
1324 ix->oldv = lj_tab_get(J->L, t, &ix->keyv); /* Lookup previous value. */
1325 *rbref = 0;
1326 rbguard->irt = 0;
1327
1328 /* Integer keys are looked up in the array part first. */
1329 key = ix->key;
1330 if (tref_isnumber(key)) {
1331 int32_t k = numberVint(&ix->keyv);
1332 if (!tvisint(&ix->keyv) && numV(&ix->keyv) != (lua_Number)k)
1333 k = LJ_MAX_ASIZE;
1334 if ((MSize)k < LJ_MAX_ASIZE) { /* Potential array key? */
1335 TRef ikey = lj_opt_narrow_index(J, key);
1336 TRef asizeref = emitir(IRTI(IR_FLOAD), ix->tab, IRFL_TAB_ASIZE);
1337 if ((MSize)k < t->asize) { /* Currently an array key? */
1338 TRef arrayref;
1339 rec_idx_abc(J, asizeref, ikey, t->asize);
1340 arrayref = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_PGC), ix->tab, IRFL_TAB_ARRAY);
1341 return emitir(IRT(IR_AREF, IRT_PGC), arrayref, ikey);
1342 } else { /* Currently not in array (may be an array extension)? */
1343 emitir(IRTGI(IR_ULE), asizeref, ikey); /* Inv. bounds check. */
1344 if (k == 0 && tref_isk(key))
1345 key = lj_ir_knum_zero(J); /* Canonicalize 0 or +-0.0 to +0.0. */
1346 /* And continue with the hash lookup. */
1347 }
1348 } else if (!tref_isk(key)) {
1349 /* We can rule out const numbers which failed the integerness test
1350 ** above. But all other numbers are potential array keys.
1351 */
1352 if (t->asize == 0) { /* True sparse tables have an empty array part. */
1353 /* Guard that the array part stays empty. */
1354 TRef tmp = emitir(IRTI(IR_FLOAD), ix->tab, IRFL_TAB_ASIZE);
1355 emitir(IRTGI(IR_EQ), tmp, lj_ir_kint(J, 0));
1356 } else {
1357 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NYITMIX);
1358 }
1359 }
1360 }
1361
1362 /* Otherwise the key is located in the hash part. */
1363 if (t->hmask == 0) { /* Shortcut for empty hash part. */
1364 /* Guard that the hash part stays empty. */
1365 TRef tmp = emitir(IRTI(IR_FLOAD), ix->tab, IRFL_TAB_HMASK);
1366 emitir(IRTGI(IR_EQ), tmp, lj_ir_kint(J, 0));
1367 return lj_ir_kkptr(J, niltvg(J2G(J)));
1368 }
1369 if (tref_isinteger(key)) /* Hash keys are based on numbers, not ints. */
1370 key = emitir(IRTN(IR_CONV), key, IRCONV_NUM_INT);
1371 if (tref_isk(key)) {
1372 /* Optimize lookup of constant hash keys. */
1373 MSize hslot = (MSize)((char *)ix->oldv - (char *)&noderef(t->node)[0].val);
1374 if (t->hmask > 0 && hslot <= t->hmask*(MSize)sizeof(Node) &&
1375 hslot <= 65535*(MSize)sizeof(Node)) {
1376 TRef node, kslot, hm;
1377 *rbref = J->cur.nins; /* Mark possible rollback point. */
1378 *rbguard = J->guardemit;
1379 hm = emitir(IRTI(IR_FLOAD), ix->tab, IRFL_TAB_HMASK);
1380 emitir(IRTGI(IR_EQ), hm, lj_ir_kint(J, (int32_t)t->hmask));
1381 node = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_PGC), ix->tab, IRFL_TAB_NODE);
1382 kslot = lj_ir_kslot(J, key, hslot / sizeof(Node));
1383 return emitir(IRTG(IR_HREFK, IRT_PGC), node, kslot);
1384 }
1385 }
1386 /* Fall back to a regular hash lookup. */
1387 return emitir(IRT(IR_HREF, IRT_PGC), ix->tab, key);
1388}
1389
1390/* Determine whether a key is NOT one of the fast metamethod names. */
1391static int nommstr(jit_State *J, TRef key)
1392{
1393 if (tref_isstr(key)) {
1394 if (tref_isk(key)) {
1395 GCstr *str = ir_kstr(IR(tref_ref(key)));
1396 uint32_t mm;
1397 for (mm = 0; mm <= MM_FAST; mm++)
1398 if (mmname_str(J2G(J), mm) == str)
1399 return 0; /* MUST be one the fast metamethod names. */
1400 } else {
1401 return 0; /* Variable string key MAY be a metamethod name. */
1402 }
1403 }
1404 return 1; /* CANNOT be a metamethod name. */
1405}
1406
1407/* Record indexed load/store. */
1408TRef lj_record_idx(jit_State *J, RecordIndex *ix)
1409{
1410 TRef xref;
1411 IROp xrefop, loadop;
1412 IRRef rbref;
1413 IRType1 rbguard;
1414 cTValue *oldv;
1415
1416 while (!tref_istab(ix->tab)) { /* Handle non-table lookup. */
1417 /* Never call raw lj_record_idx() on non-table. */
1418 lj_assertJ(ix->idxchain != 0, "bad usage");
1419 if (!lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, ix->val ? MM_newindex : MM_index))
1420 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_NOMM);
1421 handlemm:
1422 if (tref_isfunc(ix->mobj)) { /* Handle metamethod call. */
1423 BCReg func = rec_mm_prep(J, ix->val ? lj_cont_nop : lj_cont_ra);
1424 TRef *base = J->base + func + LJ_FR2;
1425 TValue *tv = J->L->base + func + LJ_FR2;
1426 base[-LJ_FR2] = ix->mobj; base[1] = ix->tab; base[2] = ix->key;
1427 setfuncV(J->L, tv-LJ_FR2, funcV(&ix->mobjv));
1428 copyTV(J->L, tv+1, &ix->tabv);
1429 copyTV(J->L, tv+2, &ix->keyv);
1430 if (ix->val) {
1431 base[3] = ix->val;
1432 copyTV(J->L, tv+3, &ix->valv);
1433 lj_record_call(J, func, 3); /* mobj(tab, key, val) */
1434 return 0;
1435 } else {
1436 lj_record_call(J, func, 2); /* res = mobj(tab, key) */
1437 return 0; /* No result yet. */
1438 }
1439 }
1440 /* Otherwise retry lookup with metaobject. */
1441 ix->tab = ix->mobj;
1442 copyTV(J->L, &ix->tabv, &ix->mobjv);
1443 if (--ix->idxchain == 0)
1444 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_IDXLOOP);
1445 }
1446
1447 /* First catch nil and NaN keys for tables. */
1448 if (tvisnil(&ix->keyv) || (tvisnum(&ix->keyv) && tvisnan(&ix->keyv))) {
1449 if (ix->val) /* Better fail early. */
1450 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_STORENN);
1451 if (tref_isk(ix->key)) {
1452 if (ix->idxchain && lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, MM_index))
1453 goto handlemm;
1454 return TREF_NIL;
1455 }
1456 }
1457
1458 /* Record the key lookup. */
1459 xref = rec_idx_key(J, ix, &rbref, &rbguard);
1460 xrefop = IR(tref_ref(xref))->o;
1461 loadop = xrefop == IR_AREF ? IR_ALOAD : IR_HLOAD;
1462 /* The lj_meta_tset() inconsistency is gone, but better play safe. */
1463 oldv = xrefop == IR_KKPTR ? (cTValue *)ir_kptr(IR(tref_ref(xref))) : ix->oldv;
1464
1465 if (ix->val == 0) { /* Indexed load */
1466 IRType t = itype2irt(oldv);
1467 TRef res;
1468 if (oldv == niltvg(J2G(J))) {
1469 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_PGC), xref, lj_ir_kkptr(J, niltvg(J2G(J))));
1470 res = TREF_NIL;
1471 } else {
1472 res = emitir(IRTG(loadop, t), xref, 0);
1473 }
1474 if (tref_ref(res) < rbref) { /* HREFK + load forwarded? */
1475 lj_ir_rollback(J, rbref); /* Rollback to eliminate hmask guard. */
1476 J->guardemit = rbguard;
1477 }
1478 if (t == IRT_NIL && ix->idxchain && lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, MM_index))
1479 goto handlemm;
1480 if (irtype_ispri(t)) res = TREF_PRI(t); /* Canonicalize primitives. */
1481 return res;
1482 } else { /* Indexed store. */
1483 GCtab *mt = tabref(tabV(&ix->tabv)->metatable);
1484 int keybarrier = tref_isgcv(ix->key) && !tref_isnil(ix->val);
1485 if (tref_ref(xref) < rbref) { /* HREFK forwarded? */
1486 lj_ir_rollback(J, rbref); /* Rollback to eliminate hmask guard. */
1487 J->guardemit = rbguard;
1488 }
1489 if (tvisnil(oldv)) { /* Previous value was nil? */
1490 /* Need to duplicate the hasmm check for the early guards. */
1491 int hasmm = 0;
1492 if (ix->idxchain && mt) {
1493 cTValue *mo = lj_tab_getstr(mt, mmname_str(J2G(J), MM_newindex));
1494 hasmm = mo && !tvisnil(mo);
1495 }
1496 if (hasmm)
1497 emitir(IRTG(loadop, IRT_NIL), xref, 0); /* Guard for nil value. */
1498 else if (xrefop == IR_HREF)
1499 emitir(IRTG(oldv == niltvg(J2G(J)) ? IR_EQ : IR_NE, IRT_PGC),
1500 xref, lj_ir_kkptr(J, niltvg(J2G(J))));
1501 if (ix->idxchain && lj_record_mm_lookup(J, ix, MM_newindex)) {
1502 lj_assertJ(hasmm, "inconsistent metamethod handling");
1503 goto handlemm;
1504 }
1505 lj_assertJ(!hasmm, "inconsistent metamethod handling");
1506 if (oldv == niltvg(J2G(J))) { /* Need to insert a new key. */
1507 TRef key = ix->key;
1508 if (tref_isinteger(key)) /* NEWREF needs a TValue as a key. */
1509 key = emitir(IRTN(IR_CONV), key, IRCONV_NUM_INT);
1510 xref = emitir(IRT(IR_NEWREF, IRT_PGC), ix->tab, key);
1511 keybarrier = 0; /* NEWREF already takes care of the key barrier. */
1512#ifdef LUAJIT_ENABLE_TABLE_BUMP
1513 if ((J->flags & JIT_F_OPT_SINK)) /* Avoid a separate flag. */
1514 rec_idx_bump(J, ix);
1515#endif
1516 }
1517 } else if (!lj_opt_fwd_wasnonnil(J, loadop, tref_ref(xref))) {
1518 /* Cannot derive that the previous value was non-nil, must do checks. */
1519 if (xrefop == IR_HREF) /* Guard against store to niltv. */
1520 emitir(IRTG(IR_NE, IRT_PGC), xref, lj_ir_kkptr(J, niltvg(J2G(J))));
1521 if (ix->idxchain) { /* Metamethod lookup required? */
1522 /* A check for NULL metatable is cheaper (hoistable) than a load. */
1523 if (!mt) {
1524 TRef mtref = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_TAB), ix->tab, IRFL_TAB_META);
1525 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_TAB), mtref, lj_ir_knull(J, IRT_TAB));
1526 } else {
1527 IRType t = itype2irt(oldv);
1528 emitir(IRTG(loadop, t), xref, 0); /* Guard for non-nil value. */
1529 }
1530 }
1531 } else {
1532 keybarrier = 0; /* Previous non-nil value kept the key alive. */
1533 }
1534 /* Convert int to number before storing. */
1535 if (!LJ_DUALNUM && tref_isinteger(ix->val))
1536 ix->val = emitir(IRTN(IR_CONV), ix->val, IRCONV_NUM_INT);
1537 emitir(IRT(loadop+IRDELTA_L2S, tref_type(ix->val)), xref, ix->val);
1538 if (keybarrier || tref_isgcv(ix->val))
1539 emitir(IRT(IR_TBAR, IRT_NIL), ix->tab, 0);
1540 /* Invalidate neg. metamethod cache for stores with certain string keys. */
1541 if (!nommstr(J, ix->key)) {
1542 TRef fref = emitir(IRT(IR_FREF, IRT_PGC), ix->tab, IRFL_TAB_NOMM);
1543 emitir(IRT(IR_FSTORE, IRT_U8), fref, lj_ir_kint(J, 0));
1544 }
1545 J->needsnap = 1;
1546 return 0;
1547 }
1548}
1549
1550static void rec_tsetm(jit_State *J, BCReg ra, BCReg rn, int32_t i)
1551{
1552 RecordIndex ix;
1553 cTValue *basev = J->L->base;
1554 GCtab *t = tabV(&basev[ra-1]);
1555 settabV(J->L, &ix.tabv, t);
1556 ix.tab = getslot(J, ra-1);
1557 ix.idxchain = 0;
1558#ifdef LUAJIT_ENABLE_TABLE_BUMP
1559 if ((J->flags & JIT_F_OPT_SINK)) {
1560 if (t->asize < i+rn-ra)
1561 lj_tab_reasize(J->L, t, i+rn-ra);
1562 setnilV(&ix.keyv);
1563 rec_idx_bump(J, &ix);
1564 }
1565#endif
1566 for (; ra < rn; i++, ra++) {
1567 setintV(&ix.keyv, i);
1568 ix.key = lj_ir_kint(J, i);
1569 copyTV(J->L, &ix.valv, &basev[ra]);
1570 ix.val = getslot(J, ra);
1571 lj_record_idx(J, &ix);
1572 }
1573}
1574
1575/* -- Upvalue access ------------------------------------------------------ */
1576
1577/* Check whether upvalue is immutable and ok to constify. */
1578static int rec_upvalue_constify(jit_State *J, GCupval *uvp)
1579{
1580 if (uvp->immutable) {
1581 cTValue *o = uvval(uvp);
1582 /* Don't constify objects that may retain large amounts of memory. */
1583#if LJ_HASFFI
1584 if (tviscdata(o)) {
1585 GCcdata *cd = cdataV(o);
1586 if (!cdataisv(cd) && !(cd->marked & LJ_GC_CDATA_FIN)) {
1587 CType *ct = ctype_raw(ctype_ctsG(J2G(J)), cd->ctypeid);
1588 if (!ctype_hassize(ct->info) || ct->size <= 16)
1589 return 1;
1590 }
1591 return 0;
1592 }
1593#else
1594 UNUSED(J);
1595#endif
1596 if (!(tvistab(o) || tvisudata(o) || tvisthread(o)))
1597 return 1;
1598 }
1599 return 0;
1600}
1601
1602/* Record upvalue load/store. */
1603static TRef rec_upvalue(jit_State *J, uint32_t uv, TRef val)
1604{
1605 GCupval *uvp = &gcref(J->fn->l.uvptr[uv])->uv;
1606 TRef fn = getcurrf(J);
1607 IRRef uref;
1608 int needbarrier = 0;
1609 if (rec_upvalue_constify(J, uvp)) { /* Try to constify immutable upvalue. */
1610 TRef tr, kfunc;
1611 lj_assertJ(val == 0, "bad usage");
1612 if (!tref_isk(fn)) { /* Late specialization of current function. */
1613 if (J->pt->flags >= PROTO_CLC_POLY)
1614 goto noconstify;
1615 kfunc = lj_ir_kfunc(J, J->fn);
1616 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_FUNC), fn, kfunc);
1617#if LJ_FR2
1618 J->base[-2] = kfunc;
1619#else
1620 J->base[-1] = kfunc | TREF_FRAME;
1621#endif
1622 fn = kfunc;
1623 }
1624 tr = lj_record_constify(J, uvval(uvp));
1625 if (tr)
1626 return tr;
1627 }
1628noconstify:
1629 /* Note: this effectively limits LJ_MAX_UPVAL to 127. */
1630 uv = (uv << 8) | (hashrot(uvp->dhash, uvp->dhash + HASH_BIAS) & 0xff);
1631 if (!uvp->closed) {
1632 uref = tref_ref(emitir(IRTG(IR_UREFO, IRT_PGC), fn, uv));
1633 /* In current stack? */
1634 if (uvval(uvp) >= tvref(J->L->stack) &&
1635 uvval(uvp) < tvref(J->L->maxstack)) {
1636 int32_t slot = (int32_t)(uvval(uvp) - (J->L->base - J->baseslot));
1637 if (slot >= 0) { /* Aliases an SSA slot? */
1638 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_PGC),
1639 REF_BASE,
1640 emitir(IRT(IR_ADD, IRT_PGC), uref,
1641 lj_ir_kint(J, (slot - 1 - LJ_FR2) * -8)));
1642 slot -= (int32_t)J->baseslot; /* Note: slot number may be negative! */
1643 if (val == 0) {
1644 return getslot(J, slot);
1645 } else {
1646 J->base[slot] = val;
1647 if (slot >= (int32_t)J->maxslot) J->maxslot = (BCReg)(slot+1);
1648 return 0;
1649 }
1650 }
1651 }
1652 emitir(IRTG(IR_UGT, IRT_PGC),
1653 emitir(IRT(IR_SUB, IRT_PGC), uref, REF_BASE),
1654 lj_ir_kint(J, (J->baseslot + J->maxslot) * 8));
1655 } else {
1656 needbarrier = 1;
1657 uref = tref_ref(emitir(IRTG(IR_UREFC, IRT_PGC), fn, uv));
1658 }
1659 if (val == 0) { /* Upvalue load */
1660 IRType t = itype2irt(uvval(uvp));
1661 TRef res = emitir(IRTG(IR_ULOAD, t), uref, 0);
1662 if (irtype_ispri(t)) res = TREF_PRI(t); /* Canonicalize primitive refs. */
1663 return res;
1664 } else { /* Upvalue store. */
1665 /* Convert int to number before storing. */
1666 if (!LJ_DUALNUM && tref_isinteger(val))
1667 val = emitir(IRTN(IR_CONV), val, IRCONV_NUM_INT);
1668 emitir(IRT(IR_USTORE, tref_type(val)), uref, val);
1669 if (needbarrier && tref_isgcv(val))
1670 emitir(IRT(IR_OBAR, IRT_NIL), uref, val);
1671 J->needsnap = 1;
1672 return 0;
1673 }
1674}
1675
1676/* -- Record calls to Lua functions --------------------------------------- */
1677
1678/* Check unroll limits for calls. */
1679static void check_call_unroll(jit_State *J, TraceNo lnk)
1680{
1681 cTValue *frame = J->L->base - 1;
1682 void *pc = mref(frame_func(frame)->l.pc, void);
1683 int32_t depth = J->framedepth;
1684 int32_t count = 0;
1685 if ((J->pt->flags & PROTO_VARARG)) depth--; /* Vararg frame still missing. */
1686 for (; depth > 0; depth--) { /* Count frames with same prototype. */
1687 if (frame_iscont(frame)) depth--;
1688 frame = frame_prev(frame);
1689 if (mref(frame_func(frame)->l.pc, void) == pc)
1690 count++;
1691 }
1692 if (J->pc == J->startpc) {
1693 if (count + J->tailcalled > J->param[JIT_P_recunroll]) {
1694 J->pc++;
1695 if (J->framedepth + J->retdepth == 0)
1696 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_TAILREC, J->cur.traceno); /* Tail-rec. */
1697 else
1698 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_UPREC, J->cur.traceno); /* Up-recursion. */
1699 }
1700 } else {
1701 if (count > J->param[JIT_P_callunroll]) {
1702 if (lnk) { /* Possible tail- or up-recursion. */
1703 lj_trace_flush(J, lnk); /* Flush trace that only returns. */
1704 /* Set a small, pseudo-random hotcount for a quick retry of JFUNC*. */
1705 hotcount_set(J2GG(J), J->pc+1, lj_prng_u64(&J2G(J)->prng) & 15u);
1706 }
1707 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_CUNROLL);
1708 }
1709 }
1710}
1711
1712/* Record Lua function setup. */
1713static void rec_func_setup(jit_State *J)
1714{
1715 GCproto *pt = J->pt;
1716 BCReg s, numparams = pt->numparams;
1717 if ((pt->flags & PROTO_NOJIT))
1718 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_CJITOFF);
1719 if (J->baseslot + pt->framesize >= LJ_MAX_JSLOTS)
1720 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_STACKOV);
1721 /* Fill up missing parameters with nil. */
1722 for (s = J->maxslot; s < numparams; s++)
1723 J->base[s] = TREF_NIL;
1724 /* The remaining slots should never be read before they are written. */
1725 J->maxslot = numparams;
1726}
1727
1728/* Record Lua vararg function setup. */
1729static void rec_func_vararg(jit_State *J)
1730{
1731 GCproto *pt = J->pt;
1732 BCReg s, fixargs, vframe = J->maxslot+1+LJ_FR2;
1733 lj_assertJ((pt->flags & PROTO_VARARG), "FUNCV in non-vararg function");
1734 if (J->baseslot + vframe + pt->framesize >= LJ_MAX_JSLOTS)
1735 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_STACKOV);
1736 J->base[vframe-1-LJ_FR2] = J->base[-1-LJ_FR2]; /* Copy function up. */
1737#if LJ_FR2
1738 J->base[vframe-1] = TREF_FRAME;
1739#endif
1740 /* Copy fixarg slots up and set their original slots to nil. */
1741 fixargs = pt->numparams < J->maxslot ? pt->numparams : J->maxslot;
1742 for (s = 0; s < fixargs; s++) {
1743 J->base[vframe+s] = J->base[s];
1744 J->base[s] = TREF_NIL;
1745 }
1746 J->maxslot = fixargs;
1747 J->framedepth++;
1748 J->base += vframe;
1749 J->baseslot += vframe;
1750}
1751
1752/* Record entry to a Lua function. */
1753static void rec_func_lua(jit_State *J)
1754{
1755 rec_func_setup(J);
1756 check_call_unroll(J, 0);
1757}
1758
1759/* Record entry to an already compiled function. */
1760static void rec_func_jit(jit_State *J, TraceNo lnk)
1761{
1762 GCtrace *T;
1763 rec_func_setup(J);
1764 T = traceref(J, lnk);
1765 if (T->linktype == LJ_TRLINK_RETURN) { /* Trace returns to interpreter? */
1766 check_call_unroll(J, lnk);
1767 /* Temporarily unpatch JFUNC* to continue recording across function. */
1768 J->patchins = *J->pc;
1769 J->patchpc = (BCIns *)J->pc;
1770 *J->patchpc = T->startins;
1771 return;
1772 }
1773 J->instunroll = 0; /* Cannot continue across a compiled function. */
1774 if (J->pc == J->startpc && J->framedepth + J->retdepth == 0)
1775 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_TAILREC, J->cur.traceno); /* Extra tail-rec. */
1776 else
1777 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_ROOT, lnk); /* Link to the function. */
1778}
1779
1780/* -- Vararg handling ----------------------------------------------------- */
1781
1782/* Detect y = select(x, ...) idiom. */
1783static int select_detect(jit_State *J)
1784{
1785 BCIns ins = J->pc[1];
1786 if (bc_op(ins) == BC_CALLM && bc_b(ins) == 2 && bc_c(ins) == 1) {
1787 cTValue *func = &J->L->base[bc_a(ins)];
1788 if (tvisfunc(func) && funcV(func)->c.ffid == FF_select) {
1789 TRef kfunc = lj_ir_kfunc(J, funcV(func));
1790 emitir(IRTG(IR_EQ, IRT_FUNC), getslot(J, bc_a(ins)), kfunc);
1791 return 1;
1792 }
1793 }
1794 return 0;
1795}
1796
1797/* Record vararg instruction. */
1798static void rec_varg(jit_State *J, BCReg dst, ptrdiff_t nresults)
1799{
1800 int32_t numparams = J->pt->numparams;
1801 ptrdiff_t nvararg = frame_delta(J->L->base-1) - numparams - 1 - LJ_FR2;
1802 lj_assertJ(frame_isvarg(J->L->base-1), "VARG in non-vararg frame");
1803 if (LJ_FR2 && dst > J->maxslot)
1804 J->base[dst-1] = 0; /* Prevent resurrection of unrelated slot. */
1805 if (J->framedepth > 0) { /* Simple case: varargs defined on-trace. */
1806 ptrdiff_t i;
1807 if (nvararg < 0) nvararg = 0;
1808 if (nresults == -1) {
1809 nresults = nvararg;
1810 J->maxslot = dst + (BCReg)nvararg;
1811 } else if (dst + nresults > J->maxslot) {
1812 J->maxslot = dst + (BCReg)nresults;
1813 }
1814 for (i = 0; i < nresults; i++)
1815 J->base[dst+i] = i < nvararg ? getslot(J, i - nvararg - 1 - LJ_FR2) : TREF_NIL;
1816 } else { /* Unknown number of varargs passed to trace. */
1817 TRef fr = emitir(IRTI(IR_SLOAD), LJ_FR2, IRSLOAD_READONLY|IRSLOAD_FRAME);
1818 int32_t frofs = 8*(1+LJ_FR2+numparams)+FRAME_VARG;
1819 if (nresults >= 0) { /* Known fixed number of results. */
1820 ptrdiff_t i;
1821 if (nvararg > 0) {
1822 ptrdiff_t nload = nvararg >= nresults ? nresults : nvararg;
1823 TRef vbase;
1824 if (nvararg >= nresults)
1825 emitir(IRTGI(IR_GE), fr, lj_ir_kint(J, frofs+8*(int32_t)nresults));
1826 else
1827 emitir(IRTGI(IR_EQ), fr,
1828 lj_ir_kint(J, (int32_t)frame_ftsz(J->L->base-1)));
1829 vbase = emitir(IRT(IR_SUB, IRT_IGC), REF_BASE, fr);
1830 vbase = emitir(IRT(IR_ADD, IRT_PGC), vbase, lj_ir_kint(J, frofs-8));
1831 for (i = 0; i < nload; i++) {
1832 IRType t = itype2irt(&J->L->base[i-1-LJ_FR2-nvararg]);
1833 TRef aref = emitir(IRT(IR_AREF, IRT_PGC),
1834 vbase, lj_ir_kint(J, (int32_t)i));
1835 TRef tr = emitir(IRTG(IR_VLOAD, t), aref, 0);
1836 if (irtype_ispri(t)) tr = TREF_PRI(t); /* Canonicalize primitives. */
1837 J->base[dst+i] = tr;
1838 }
1839 } else {
1840 emitir(IRTGI(IR_LE), fr, lj_ir_kint(J, frofs));
1841 nvararg = 0;
1842 }
1843 for (i = nvararg; i < nresults; i++)
1844 J->base[dst+i] = TREF_NIL;
1845 if (dst + (BCReg)nresults > J->maxslot)
1846 J->maxslot = dst + (BCReg)nresults;
1847 } else if (select_detect(J)) { /* y = select(x, ...) */
1848 TRef tridx = J->base[dst-1];
1849 TRef tr = TREF_NIL;
1850 ptrdiff_t idx = lj_ffrecord_select_mode(J, tridx, &J->L->base[dst-1]);
1851 if (idx < 0) goto nyivarg;
1852 if (idx != 0 && !tref_isinteger(tridx))
1853 tridx = emitir(IRTGI(IR_CONV), tridx, IRCONV_INT_NUM|IRCONV_INDEX);
1854 if (idx != 0 && tref_isk(tridx)) {
1855 emitir(IRTGI(idx <= nvararg ? IR_GE : IR_LT),
1856 fr, lj_ir_kint(J, frofs+8*(int32_t)idx));
1857 frofs -= 8; /* Bias for 1-based index. */
1858 } else if (idx <= nvararg) { /* Compute size. */
1859 TRef tmp = emitir(IRTI(IR_ADD), fr, lj_ir_kint(J, -frofs));
1860 if (numparams)
1861 emitir(IRTGI(IR_GE), tmp, lj_ir_kint(J, 0));
1862 tr = emitir(IRTI(IR_BSHR), tmp, lj_ir_kint(J, 3));
1863 if (idx != 0) {
1864 tridx = emitir(IRTI(IR_ADD), tridx, lj_ir_kint(J, -1));
1865 rec_idx_abc(J, tr, tridx, (uint32_t)nvararg);
1866 }
1867 } else {
1868 TRef tmp = lj_ir_kint(J, frofs);
1869 if (idx != 0) {
1870 TRef tmp2 = emitir(IRTI(IR_BSHL), tridx, lj_ir_kint(J, 3));
1871 tmp = emitir(IRTI(IR_ADD), tmp2, tmp);
1872 } else {
1873 tr = lj_ir_kint(J, 0);
1874 }
1875 emitir(IRTGI(IR_LT), fr, tmp);
1876 }
1877 if (idx != 0 && idx <= nvararg) {
1878 IRType t;
1879 TRef aref, vbase = emitir(IRT(IR_SUB, IRT_IGC), REF_BASE, fr);
1880 vbase = emitir(IRT(IR_ADD, IRT_PGC), vbase,
1881 lj_ir_kint(J, frofs-(8<<LJ_FR2)));
1882 t = itype2irt(&J->L->base[idx-2-LJ_FR2-nvararg]);
1883 aref = emitir(IRT(IR_AREF, IRT_PGC), vbase, tridx);
1884 tr = emitir(IRTG(IR_VLOAD, t), aref, 0);
1885 if (irtype_ispri(t)) tr = TREF_PRI(t); /* Canonicalize primitives. */
1886 }
1887 J->base[dst-2-LJ_FR2] = tr;
1888 J->maxslot = dst-1-LJ_FR2;
1889 J->bcskip = 2; /* Skip CALLM + select. */
1890 } else {
1891 nyivarg:
1892 setintV(&J->errinfo, BC_VARG);
1893 lj_trace_err_info(J, LJ_TRERR_NYIBC);
1894 }
1895 }
1896 if (J->baseslot + J->maxslot >= LJ_MAX_JSLOTS)
1897 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_STACKOV);
1898}
