1900/* -- Record allocations -------------------------------------------------- */
1901
1902static TRef rec_tnew(jit_State *J, uint32_t ah)
1903{
1904 uint32_t asize = ah & 0x7ff;
1905 uint32_t hbits = ah >> 11;
1906 TRef tr;
1907 if (asize == 0x7ff) asize = 0x801;
1908 tr = emitir(IRTG(IR_TNEW, IRT_TAB), asize, hbits);
1909#ifdef LUAJIT_ENABLE_TABLE_BUMP
1910 J->rbchash[(tr & (RBCHASH_SLOTS-1))].ref = tref_ref(tr);
1911 setmref(J->rbchash[(tr & (RBCHASH_SLOTS-1))].pc, J->pc);
1912 setgcref(J->rbchash[(tr & (RBCHASH_SLOTS-1))].pt, obj2gco(J->pt));
1913#endif
1914 return tr;
1915}
1916
1917/* -- Concatenation ------------------------------------------------------- */
1918
1919static TRef rec_cat(jit_State *J, BCReg baseslot, BCReg topslot)
1920{
1921 TRef *top = &J->base[topslot];
1922 TValue savetv[5];
1923 BCReg s;
1924 RecordIndex ix;
1925 lj_assertJ(baseslot < topslot, "bad CAT arg");
1926 for (s = baseslot; s <= topslot; s++)
1927 (void)getslot(J, s); /* Ensure all arguments have a reference. */
1928 if (tref_isnumber_str(top[0]) && tref_isnumber_str(top[-1])) {
1929 TRef tr, hdr, *trp, *xbase, *base = &J->base[baseslot];
1930 /* First convert numbers to strings. */
1931 for (trp = top; trp >= base; trp--) {
1932 if (tref_isnumber(*trp))
1933 *trp = emitir(IRT(IR_TOSTR, IRT_STR), *trp,
1934 tref_isnum(*trp) ? IRTOSTR_NUM : IRTOSTR_INT);
1935 else if (!tref_isstr(*trp))
1936 break;
1937 }
1938 xbase = ++trp;
1939 tr = hdr = emitir(IRT(IR_BUFHDR, IRT_PGC),
1940 lj_ir_kptr(J, &J2G(J)->tmpbuf), IRBUFHDR_RESET);
1941 do {
1942 tr = emitir(IRTG(IR_BUFPUT, IRT_PGC), tr, *trp++);
1943 } while (trp <= top);
1944 tr = emitir(IRTG(IR_BUFSTR, IRT_STR), tr, hdr);
1945 J->maxslot = (BCReg)(xbase - J->base);
1946 if (xbase == base) return tr; /* Return simple concatenation result. */
1947 /* Pass partial result. */
1948 topslot = J->maxslot--;
1949 *xbase = tr;
1950 top = xbase;
1951 setstrV(J->L, &ix.keyv, &J2G(J)->strempty); /* Simulate string result. */
1952 } else {
1953 J->maxslot = topslot-1;
1954 copyTV(J->L, &ix.keyv, &J->L->base[topslot]);
1955 }
1956 copyTV(J->L, &ix.tabv, &J->L->base[topslot-1]);
1957 ix.tab = top[-1];
1958 ix.key = top[0];
1959 memcpy(savetv, &J->L->base[topslot-1], sizeof(savetv)); /* Save slots. */
1960 rec_mm_arith(J, &ix, MM_concat); /* Call __concat metamethod. */
1961 memcpy(&J->L->base[topslot-1], savetv, sizeof(savetv)); /* Restore slots. */
1962 return 0; /* No result yet. */
1963}
1964
1965/* -- Record bytecode ops ------------------------------------------------- */
1966
1967/* Prepare for comparison. */
1968static void rec_comp_prep(jit_State *J)
1969{
1970 /* Prevent merging with snapshot #0 (GC exit) since we fixup the PC. */
1971 if (J->cur.nsnap == 1 && J->cur.snap[0].ref == J->cur.nins)
1972 emitir_raw(IRT(IR_NOP, IRT_NIL), 0, 0);
1973 lj_snap_add(J);
1974}
1975
1976/* Fixup comparison. */
1977static void rec_comp_fixup(jit_State *J, const BCIns *pc, int cond)
1978{
1979 BCIns jmpins = pc[1];
1980 const BCIns *npc = pc + 2 + (cond ? bc_j(jmpins) : 0);
1981 SnapShot *snap = &J->cur.snap[J->cur.nsnap-1];
1982 /* Set PC to opposite target to avoid re-recording the comp. in side trace. */
1983#if LJ_FR2
1984 SnapEntry *flink = &J->cur.snapmap[snap->mapofs + snap->nent];
1985 uint64_t pcbase;
1986 memcpy(&pcbase, flink, sizeof(uint64_t));
1987 pcbase = (pcbase & 0xff) | (u64ptr(npc) << 8);
1988 memcpy(flink, &pcbase, sizeof(uint64_t));
1989#else
1990 J->cur.snapmap[snap->mapofs + snap->nent] = SNAP_MKPC(npc);
1991#endif
1992 J->needsnap = 1;
1993 if (bc_a(jmpins) < J->maxslot) J->maxslot = bc_a(jmpins);
1994 lj_snap_shrink(J); /* Shrink last snapshot if possible. */
1995}
1996
1997/* Record the next bytecode instruction (_before_ it's executed). */
1998void lj_record_ins(jit_State *J)
1999{
2000 cTValue *lbase;
2001 RecordIndex ix;
2002 const BCIns *pc;
2003 BCIns ins;
2004 BCOp op;
2005 TRef ra, rb, rc;
2006
2007 /* Perform post-processing action before recording the next instruction. */
2008 if (LJ_UNLIKELY(J->postproc != LJ_POST_NONE)) {
2009 switch (J->postproc) {
2010 case LJ_POST_FIXCOMP: /* Fixup comparison. */
2011 pc = (const BCIns *)(uintptr_t)J2G(J)->tmptv.u64;
2012 rec_comp_fixup(J, pc, (!tvistruecond(&J2G(J)->tmptv2) ^ (bc_op(*pc)&1)));
2013 /* fallthrough */
2014 case LJ_POST_FIXGUARD: /* Fixup and emit pending guard. */
2015 case LJ_POST_FIXGUARDSNAP: /* Fixup and emit pending guard and snapshot. */
2016 if (!tvistruecond(&J2G(J)->tmptv2)) {
2017 J->fold.ins.o ^= 1; /* Flip guard to opposite. */
2018 if (J->postproc == LJ_POST_FIXGUARDSNAP) {
2019 SnapShot *snap = &J->cur.snap[J->cur.nsnap-1];
2020 J->cur.snapmap[snap->mapofs+snap->nent-1]--; /* False -> true. */
2021 }
2022 }
2023 lj_opt_fold(J); /* Emit pending guard. */
2024 /* fallthrough */
2025 case LJ_POST_FIXBOOL:
2026 if (!tvistruecond(&J2G(J)->tmptv2)) {
2027 BCReg s;
2028 TValue *tv = J->L->base;
2029 for (s = 0; s < J->maxslot; s++) /* Fixup stack slot (if any). */
2030 if (J->base[s] == TREF_TRUE && tvisfalse(&tv[s])) {
2031 J->base[s] = TREF_FALSE;
2032 break;
2033 }
2034 }
2035 break;
2036 case LJ_POST_FIXCONST:
2037 {
2038 BCReg s;
2039 TValue *tv = J->L->base;
2040 for (s = 0; s < J->maxslot; s++) /* Constify stack slots (if any). */
2041 if (J->base[s] == TREF_NIL && !tvisnil(&tv[s]))
2042 J->base[s] = lj_record_constify(J, &tv[s]);
2043 }
2044 break;
2045 case LJ_POST_FFRETRY: /* Suppress recording of retried fast function. */
2046 if (bc_op(*J->pc) >= BC__MAX)
2047 return;
2048 break;
2049 default: lj_assertJ(0, "bad post-processing mode"); break;
2050 }
2051 J->postproc = LJ_POST_NONE;
2052 }
2053
2054 /* Need snapshot before recording next bytecode (e.g. after a store). */
2055 if (J->needsnap) {
2056 J->needsnap = 0;
2057 if (J->pt) lj_snap_purge(J);
2058 lj_snap_add(J);
2059 J->mergesnap = 1;
2060 }
2061
2062 /* Skip some bytecodes. */
2063 if (LJ_UNLIKELY(J->bcskip > 0)) {
2064 J->bcskip--;
2065 return;
2066 }
2067
2068 /* Record only closed loops for root traces. */
2069 pc = J->pc;
2070 if (J->framedepth == 0 &&
2071 (MSize)((char *)pc - (char *)J->bc_min) >= J->bc_extent)
2072 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_LLEAVE);
2073
2074#ifdef LUA_USE_ASSERT
2075 rec_check_slots(J);
2076 rec_check_ir(J);
2077#endif
2078
2079#if LJ_HASPROFILE
2080 rec_profile_ins(J, pc);
2081#endif
2082
2083 /* Keep a copy of the runtime values of var/num/str operands. */
2084#define rav (&ix.valv)
2085#define rbv (&ix.tabv)
2086#define rcv (&ix.keyv)
2087
2088 lbase = J->L->base;
2089 ins = *pc;
2090 op = bc_op(ins);
2091 ra = bc_a(ins);
2092 ix.val = 0;
2093 switch (bcmode_a(op)) {
2094 case BCMvar:
2095 copyTV(J->L, rav, &lbase[ra]); ix.val = ra = getslot(J, ra); break;
2096 default: break; /* Handled later. */
2097 }
2098 rb = bc_b(ins);
2099 rc = bc_c(ins);
2100 switch (bcmode_b(op)) {
2101 case BCMnone: rb = 0; rc = bc_d(ins); break; /* Upgrade rc to 'rd'. */
2102 case BCMvar:
2103 copyTV(J->L, rbv, &lbase[rb]); ix.tab = rb = getslot(J, rb); break;
2104 default: break; /* Handled later. */
2105 }
2106 switch (bcmode_c(op)) {
2107 case BCMvar:
2108 copyTV(J->L, rcv, &lbase[rc]); ix.key = rc = getslot(J, rc); break;
2109 case BCMpri: setpriV(rcv, ~rc); ix.key = rc = TREF_PRI(IRT_NIL+rc); break;
2110 case BCMnum: { cTValue *tv = proto_knumtv(J->pt, rc);
2111 copyTV(J->L, rcv, tv); ix.key = rc = tvisint(tv) ? lj_ir_kint(J, intV(tv)) :
2112 lj_ir_knumint(J, numV(tv)); } break;
2113 case BCMstr: { GCstr *s = gco2str(proto_kgc(J->pt, ~(ptrdiff_t)rc));
2114 setstrV(J->L, rcv, s); ix.key = rc = lj_ir_kstr(J, s); } break;
2115 default: break; /* Handled later. */
2116 }
2117
2118 switch (op) {
2119
2120 /* -- Comparison ops ---------------------------------------------------- */
2121
2122 case BC_ISLT: case BC_ISGE: case BC_ISLE: case BC_ISGT:
2123#if LJ_HASFFI
2124 if (tref_iscdata(ra) || tref_iscdata(rc)) {
2125 rec_mm_comp_cdata(J, &ix, op, ((int)op & 2) ? MM_le : MM_lt);
2126 break;
2127 }
2128#endif
2129 /* Emit nothing for two numeric or string consts. */
2130 if (!(tref_isk2(ra,rc) && tref_isnumber_str(ra) && tref_isnumber_str(rc))) {
2131 IRType ta = tref_isinteger(ra) ? IRT_INT : tref_type(ra);
2132 IRType tc = tref_isinteger(rc) ? IRT_INT : tref_type(rc);
2133 int irop;
2134 if (ta != tc) {
2135 /* Widen mixed number/int comparisons to number/number comparison. */
2136 if (ta == IRT_INT && tc == IRT_NUM) {
2137 ra = emitir(IRTN(IR_CONV), ra, IRCONV_NUM_INT);
2138 ta = IRT_NUM;
2139 } else if (ta == IRT_NUM && tc == IRT_INT) {
2140 rc = emitir(IRTN(IR_CONV), rc, IRCONV_NUM_INT);
2141 } else if (LJ_52) {
2142 ta = IRT_NIL; /* Force metamethod for different types. */
2143 } else if (!((ta == IRT_FALSE || ta == IRT_TRUE) &&
2144 (tc == IRT_FALSE || tc == IRT_TRUE))) {
2145 break; /* Interpreter will throw for two different types. */
2146 }
2147 }
2148 rec_comp_prep(J);
2149 irop = (int)op - (int)BC_ISLT + (int)IR_LT;
2150 if (ta == IRT_NUM) {
2151 if ((irop & 1)) irop ^= 4; /* ISGE/ISGT are unordered. */
2152 if (!lj_ir_numcmp(numberVnum(rav), numberVnum(rcv), (IROp)irop))
2153 irop ^= 5;
2154 } else if (ta == IRT_INT) {
2155 if (!lj_ir_numcmp(numberVnum(rav), numberVnum(rcv), (IROp)irop))
2156 irop ^= 1;
2157 } else if (ta == IRT_STR) {
2158 if (!lj_ir_strcmp(strV(rav), strV(rcv), (IROp)irop)) irop ^= 1;
2159 ra = lj_ir_call(J, IRCALL_lj_str_cmp, ra, rc);
2160 rc = lj_ir_kint(J, 0);
2161 ta = IRT_INT;
2162 } else {
2163 rec_mm_comp(J, &ix, (int)op);
2164 break;
2165 }
2166 emitir(IRTG(irop, ta), ra, rc);
2167 rec_comp_fixup(J, J->pc, ((int)op ^ irop) & 1);
2168 }
2169 break;
2170
2171 case BC_ISEQV: case BC_ISNEV:
2172 case BC_ISEQS: case BC_ISNES:
2173 case BC_ISEQN: case BC_ISNEN:
2174 case BC_ISEQP: case BC_ISNEP:
2175#if LJ_HASFFI
2176 if (tref_iscdata(ra) || tref_iscdata(rc)) {
2177 rec_mm_comp_cdata(J, &ix, op, MM_eq);
2178 break;
2179 }
2180#endif
2181 /* Emit nothing for two non-table, non-udata consts. */
2182 if (!(tref_isk2(ra, rc) && !(tref_istab(ra) || tref_isudata(ra)))) {
2183 int diff;
2184 rec_comp_prep(J);
2185 diff = lj_record_objcmp(J, ra, rc, rav, rcv);
2186 if (diff == 2 || !(tref_istab(ra) || tref_isudata(ra)))
2187 rec_comp_fixup(J, J->pc, ((int)op & 1) == !diff);
2188 else if (diff == 1) /* Only check __eq if different, but same type. */
2189 rec_mm_equal(J, &ix, (int)op);
2190 }
2191 break;
2192
2193 /* -- Unary test and copy ops ------------------------------------------- */
2194
2195 case BC_ISTC: case BC_ISFC:
2196 if ((op & 1) == tref_istruecond(rc))
2197 rc = 0; /* Don't store if condition is not true. */
2198 /* fallthrough */
2199 case BC_IST: case BC_ISF: /* Type specialization suffices. */
2200 if (bc_a(pc[1]) < J->maxslot)
2201 J->maxslot = bc_a(pc[1]); /* Shrink used slots. */
2202 break;
2203
2204 case BC_ISTYPE: case BC_ISNUM:
2205 /* These coercions need to correspond with lj_meta_istype(). */
2206 if (LJ_DUALNUM && rc == ~LJ_TNUMX+1)
2207 ra = lj_opt_narrow_toint(J, ra);
2208 else if (rc == ~LJ_TNUMX+2)
2209 ra = lj_ir_tonum(J, ra);
2210 else if (rc == ~LJ_TSTR+1)
2211 ra = lj_ir_tostr(J, ra);
2212 /* else: type specialization suffices. */
2213 J->base[bc_a(ins)] = ra;
2214 break;
2215
2216 /* -- Unary ops --------------------------------------------------------- */
2217
2218 case BC_NOT:
2219 /* Type specialization already forces const result. */
2220 rc = tref_istruecond(rc) ? TREF_FALSE : TREF_TRUE;
2221 break;
2222
2223 case BC_LEN:
2224 if (tref_isstr(rc))
2225 rc = emitir(IRTI(IR_FLOAD), rc, IRFL_STR_LEN);
2226 else if (!LJ_52 && tref_istab(rc))
2227 rc = emitir(IRTI(IR_ALEN), rc, TREF_NIL);
2228 else
2229 rc = rec_mm_len(J, rc, rcv);
2230 break;
2231
2232 /* -- Arithmetic ops ---------------------------------------------------- */
2233
2234 case BC_UNM:
2235 if (tref_isnumber_str(rc)) {
2236 rc = lj_opt_narrow_unm(J, rc, rcv);
2237 } else {
2238 ix.tab = rc;
2239 copyTV(J->L, &ix.tabv, rcv);
2240 rc = rec_mm_arith(J, &ix, MM_unm);
2241 }
2242 break;
2243
2244 case BC_ADDNV: case BC_SUBNV: case BC_MULNV: case BC_DIVNV: case BC_MODNV:
2245 /* Swap rb/rc and rbv/rcv. rav is temp. */
2246 ix.tab = rc; ix.key = rc = rb; rb = ix.tab;
2247 copyTV(J->L, rav, rbv);
2248 copyTV(J->L, rbv, rcv);
2249 copyTV(J->L, rcv, rav);
2250 if (op == BC_MODNV)
2251 goto recmod;
2252 /* fallthrough */
2253 case BC_ADDVN: case BC_SUBVN: case BC_MULVN: case BC_DIVVN:
2254 case BC_ADDVV: case BC_SUBVV: case BC_MULVV: case BC_DIVVV: {
2255 MMS mm = bcmode_mm(op);
2256 if (tref_isnumber_str(rb) && tref_isnumber_str(rc))
2257 rc = lj_opt_narrow_arith(J, rb, rc, rbv, rcv,
2258 (int)mm - (int)MM_add + (int)IR_ADD);
2259 else
2260 rc = rec_mm_arith(J, &ix, mm);
2261 break;
2262 }
2263
2264 case BC_MODVN: case BC_MODVV:
2265 recmod:
2266 if (tref_isnumber_str(rb) && tref_isnumber_str(rc))
2267 rc = lj_opt_narrow_mod(J, rb, rc, rbv, rcv);
2268 else
2269 rc = rec_mm_arith(J, &ix, MM_mod);
2270 break;
2271
2272 case BC_POW:
2273 if (tref_isnumber_str(rb) && tref_isnumber_str(rc))
2274 rc = lj_opt_narrow_pow(J, rb, rc, rbv, rcv);
2275 else
2276 rc = rec_mm_arith(J, &ix, MM_pow);
2277 break;
2278
2279 /* -- Miscellaneous ops ------------------------------------------------- */
2280
2281 case BC_CAT:
2282 rc = rec_cat(J, rb, rc);
2283 break;
2284
2285 /* -- Constant and move ops --------------------------------------------- */
2286
2287 case BC_MOV:
2288 /* Clear gap of method call to avoid resurrecting previous refs. */
2289 if (ra > J->maxslot) {
2290#if LJ_FR2
2291 memset(J->base + J->maxslot, 0, (ra - J->maxslot) * sizeof(TRef));
2292#else
2293 J->base[ra-1] = 0;
2294#endif
2295 }
2296 break;
2297 case BC_KSTR: case BC_KNUM: case BC_KPRI:
2298 break;
2299 case BC_KSHORT:
2300 rc = lj_ir_kint(J, (int32_t)(int16_t)rc);
2301 break;
2302 case BC_KNIL:
2303 if (LJ_FR2 && ra > J->maxslot)
2304 J->base[ra-1] = 0;
2305 while (ra <= rc)
2306 J->base[ra++] = TREF_NIL;
2307 if (rc >= J->maxslot) J->maxslot = rc+1;
2308 break;
2309#if LJ_HASFFI
2310 case BC_KCDATA:
2311 rc = lj_ir_kgc(J, proto_kgc(J->pt, ~(ptrdiff_t)rc), IRT_CDATA);
2312 break;
2313#endif
2314
2315 /* -- Upvalue and function ops ------------------------------------------ */
2316
2317 case BC_UGET:
2318 rc = rec_upvalue(J, rc, 0);
2319 break;
2320 case BC_USETV: case BC_USETS: case BC_USETN: case BC_USETP:
2321 rec_upvalue(J, ra, rc);
2322 break;
2323
2324 /* -- Table ops --------------------------------------------------------- */
2325
2326 case BC_GGET: case BC_GSET:
2327 settabV(J->L, &ix.tabv, tabref(J->fn->l.env));
2328 ix.tab = emitir(IRT(IR_FLOAD, IRT_TAB), getcurrf(J), IRFL_FUNC_ENV);
2329 ix.idxchain = LJ_MAX_IDXCHAIN;
2330 rc = lj_record_idx(J, &ix);
2331 break;
2332
2333 case BC_TGETB: case BC_TSETB:
2334 setintV(&ix.keyv, (int32_t)rc);
2335 ix.key = lj_ir_kint(J, (int32_t)rc);
2336 /* fallthrough */
2337 case BC_TGETV: case BC_TGETS: case BC_TSETV: case BC_TSETS:
2338 ix.idxchain = LJ_MAX_IDXCHAIN;
2339 rc = lj_record_idx(J, &ix);
2340 break;
2341 case BC_TGETR: case BC_TSETR:
2342 ix.idxchain = 0;
2343 rc = lj_record_idx(J, &ix);
2344 break;
2345
2346 case BC_TSETM:
2347 rec_tsetm(J, ra, (BCReg)(J->L->top - J->L->base), (int32_t)rcv->u32.lo);
2348 break;
2349
2350 case BC_TNEW:
2351 rc = rec_tnew(J, rc);
2352 break;
2353 case BC_TDUP:
2354 rc = emitir(IRTG(IR_TDUP, IRT_TAB),
2355 lj_ir_ktab(J, gco2tab(proto_kgc(J->pt, ~(ptrdiff_t)rc))), 0);
2356#ifdef LUAJIT_ENABLE_TABLE_BUMP
2357 J->rbchash[(rc & (RBCHASH_SLOTS-1))].ref = tref_ref(rc);
2358 setmref(J->rbchash[(rc & (RBCHASH_SLOTS-1))].pc, pc);
2359 setgcref(J->rbchash[(rc & (RBCHASH_SLOTS-1))].pt, obj2gco(J->pt));
2360#endif
2361 break;
2362
2363 /* -- Calls and vararg handling ----------------------------------------- */
2364
2365 case BC_ITERC:
2366 J->base[ra] = getslot(J, ra-3);
2367 J->base[ra+1+LJ_FR2] = getslot(J, ra-2);
2368 J->base[ra+2+LJ_FR2] = getslot(J, ra-1);
2369 { /* Do the actual copy now because lj_record_call needs the values. */
2370 TValue *b = &J->L->base[ra];
2371 copyTV(J->L, b, b-3);
2372 copyTV(J->L, b+1+LJ_FR2, b-2);
2373 copyTV(J->L, b+2+LJ_FR2, b-1);
2374 }
2375 lj_record_call(J, ra, (ptrdiff_t)rc-1);
2376 break;
2377
2378 /* L->top is set to L->base+ra+rc+NARGS-1+1. See lj_dispatch_ins(). */
2379 case BC_CALLM:
2380 rc = (BCReg)(J->L->top - J->L->base) - ra - LJ_FR2;
2381 /* fallthrough */
2382 case BC_CALL:
2383 lj_record_call(J, ra, (ptrdiff_t)rc-1);
2384 break;
2385
2386 case BC_CALLMT:
2387 rc = (BCReg)(J->L->top - J->L->base) - ra - LJ_FR2;
2388 /* fallthrough */
2389 case BC_CALLT:
2390 lj_record_tailcall(J, ra, (ptrdiff_t)rc-1);
2391 break;
2392
2393 case BC_VARG:
2394 rec_varg(J, ra, (ptrdiff_t)rb-1);
2395 break;
2396
2397 /* -- Returns ----------------------------------------------------------- */
2398
2399 case BC_RETM:
2400 /* L->top is set to L->base+ra+rc+NRESULTS-1, see lj_dispatch_ins(). */
2401 rc = (BCReg)(J->L->top - J->L->base) - ra + 1;
2402 /* fallthrough */
2403 case BC_RET: case BC_RET0: case BC_RET1:
2404#if LJ_HASPROFILE
2405 rec_profile_ret(J);
2406#endif
2407 lj_record_ret(J, ra, (ptrdiff_t)rc-1);
2408 break;
2409
2410 /* -- Loops and branches ------------------------------------------------ */
2411
2412 case BC_FORI:
2413 if (rec_for(J, pc, 0) != LOOPEV_LEAVE)
2414 J->loopref = J->cur.nins;
2415 break;
2416 case BC_JFORI:
2417 lj_assertJ(bc_op(pc[(ptrdiff_t)rc-BCBIAS_J]) == BC_JFORL,
2418 "JFORI does not point to JFORL");
2419 if (rec_for(J, pc, 0) != LOOPEV_LEAVE) /* Link to existing loop. */
2420 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_ROOT, bc_d(pc[(ptrdiff_t)rc-BCBIAS_J]));
2421 /* Continue tracing if the loop is not entered. */
2422 break;
2423
2424 case BC_FORL:
2425 rec_loop_interp(J, pc, rec_for(J, pc+((ptrdiff_t)rc-BCBIAS_J), 1));
2426 break;
2427 case BC_ITERL:
2428 rec_loop_interp(J, pc, rec_iterl(J, *pc));
2429 break;
2430 case BC_LOOP:
2431 rec_loop_interp(J, pc, rec_loop(J, ra, 1));
2432 break;
2433
2434 case BC_JFORL:
2435 rec_loop_jit(J, rc, rec_for(J, pc+bc_j(traceref(J, rc)->startins), 1));
2436 break;
2437 case BC_JITERL:
2438 rec_loop_jit(J, rc, rec_iterl(J, traceref(J, rc)->startins));
2439 break;
2440 case BC_JLOOP:
2441 rec_loop_jit(J, rc, rec_loop(J, ra,
2442 !bc_isret(bc_op(traceref(J, rc)->startins))));
2443 break;
2444
2445 case BC_IFORL:
2446 case BC_IITERL:
2447 case BC_ILOOP:
2448 case BC_IFUNCF:
2449 case BC_IFUNCV:
2450 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_BLACKL);
2451 break;
2452
2453 case BC_JMP:
2454 if (ra < J->maxslot)
2455 J->maxslot = ra; /* Shrink used slots. */
2456 break;
2457
2458 /* -- Function headers -------------------------------------------------- */
2459
2460 case BC_FUNCF:
2461 rec_func_lua(J);
2462 break;
2463 case BC_JFUNCF:
2464 rec_func_jit(J, rc);
2465 break;
2466
2467 case BC_FUNCV:
2468 rec_func_vararg(J);
2469 rec_func_lua(J);
2470 break;
2471 case BC_JFUNCV:
2472 /* Cannot happen. No hotcall counting for varag funcs. */
2473 lj_assertJ(0, "unsupported vararg hotcall");
2474 break;
2475
2476 case BC_FUNCC:
2477 case BC_FUNCCW:
2478 lj_ffrecord_func(J);
2479 break;
2480
2481 default:
2482 if (op >= BC__MAX) {
2483 lj_ffrecord_func(J);
2484 break;
2485 }
2486 /* fallthrough */
2487 case BC_ITERN:
2488 case BC_ISNEXT:
2489 case BC_UCLO:
2490 case BC_FNEW:
2491 setintV(&J->errinfo, (int32_t)op);
2492 lj_trace_err_info(J, LJ_TRERR_NYIBC);
2493 break;
2494 }
2495
2496 /* rc == 0 if we have no result yet, e.g. pending __index metamethod call. */
2497 if (bcmode_a(op) == BCMdst && rc) {
2498 J->base[ra] = rc;
2499 if (ra >= J->maxslot) {
2500#if LJ_FR2
2501 if (ra > J->maxslot) J->base[ra-1] = 0;
2502#endif
2503 J->maxslot = ra+1;
2504 }
2505 }
2506
2507#undef rav
2508#undef rbv
2509#undef rcv
2510
2511 /* Limit the number of recorded IR instructions and constants. */
2512 if (J->cur.nins > REF_FIRST+(IRRef)J->param[JIT_P_maxrecord] ||
2513 J->cur.nk < REF_BIAS-(IRRef)J->param[JIT_P_maxirconst])
2514 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_TRACEOV);
2515}
2516
2517/* -- Recording setup ----------------------------------------------------- */
2518
2519/* Setup recording for a root trace started by a hot loop. */
2520static const BCIns *rec_setup_root(jit_State *J)
2521{
2522 /* Determine the next PC and the bytecode range for the loop. */
2523 const BCIns *pcj, *pc = J->pc;
2524 BCIns ins = *pc;
2525 BCReg ra = bc_a(ins);
2526 switch (bc_op(ins)) {
2527 case BC_FORL:
2528 J->bc_extent = (MSize)(-bc_j(ins))*sizeof(BCIns);
2529 pc += 1+bc_j(ins);
2530 J->bc_min = pc;
2531 break;
2532 case BC_ITERL:
2533 lj_assertJ(bc_op(pc[-1]) == BC_ITERC, "no ITERC before ITERL");
2534 J->maxslot = ra + bc_b(pc[-1]) - 1;
2535 J->bc_extent = (MSize)(-bc_j(ins))*sizeof(BCIns);
2536 pc += 1+bc_j(ins);
2537 lj_assertJ(bc_op(pc[-1]) == BC_JMP, "ITERL does not point to JMP+1");
2538 J->bc_min = pc;
2539 break;
2540 case BC_LOOP:
2541 /* Only check BC range for real loops, but not for "repeat until true". */
2542 pcj = pc + bc_j(ins);
2543 ins = *pcj;
2544 if (bc_op(ins) == BC_JMP && bc_j(ins) < 0) {
2545 J->bc_min = pcj+1 + bc_j(ins);
2546 J->bc_extent = (MSize)(-bc_j(ins))*sizeof(BCIns);
2547 }
2548 J->maxslot = ra;
2549 pc++;
2550 break;
2551 case BC_RET:
2552 case BC_RET0:
2553 case BC_RET1:
2554 /* No bytecode range check for down-recursive root traces. */
2555 J->maxslot = ra + bc_d(ins) - 1;
2556 break;
2557 case BC_FUNCF:
2558 /* No bytecode range check for root traces started by a hot call. */
2559 J->maxslot = J->pt->numparams;
2560 pc++;
2561 break;
2562 case BC_CALLM:
2563 case BC_CALL:
2564 case BC_ITERC:
2565 /* No bytecode range check for stitched traces. */
2566 pc++;
2567 break;
2568 default:
2569 lj_assertJ(0, "bad root trace start bytecode %d", bc_op(ins));
2570 break;
2571 }
2572 return pc;
2573}
2574
2575/* Setup for recording a new trace. */
2576void lj_record_setup(jit_State *J)
2577{
2578 uint32_t i;
2579
2580 /* Initialize state related to current trace. */
2581 memset(J->slot, 0, sizeof(J->slot));
2582 memset(J->chain, 0, sizeof(J->chain));
2583#ifdef LUAJIT_ENABLE_TABLE_BUMP
2584 memset(J->rbchash, 0, sizeof(J->rbchash));
2585#endif
2586 memset(J->bpropcache, 0, sizeof(J->bpropcache));
2587 J->scev.idx = REF_NIL;
2588 setmref(J->scev.pc, NULL);
2589
2590 J->baseslot = 1+LJ_FR2; /* Invoking function is at base[-1-LJ_FR2]. */
2591 J->base = J->slot + J->baseslot;
2592 J->maxslot = 0;
2593 J->framedepth = 0;
2594 J->retdepth = 0;
2595
2596 J->instunroll = J->param[JIT_P_instunroll];
2597 J->loopunroll = J->param[JIT_P_loopunroll];
2598 J->tailcalled = 0;
2599 J->loopref = 0;
2600
2601 J->bc_min = NULL; /* Means no limit. */
2602 J->bc_extent = ~(MSize)0;
2603
2604 /* Emit instructions for fixed references. Also triggers initial IR alloc. */
2605 emitir_raw(IRT(IR_BASE, IRT_PGC), J->parent, J->exitno);
2606 for (i = 0; i <= 2; i++) {
2607 IRIns *ir = IR(REF_NIL-i);
2608 ir->i = 0;
2609 ir->t.irt = (uint8_t)(IRT_NIL+i);
2610 ir->o = IR_KPRI;
2611 ir->prev = 0;
2612 }
2613 J->cur.nk = REF_TRUE;
2614
2615 J->startpc = J->pc;
2616 setmref(J->cur.startpc, J->pc);
2617 if (J->parent) { /* Side trace. */
2618 GCtrace *T = traceref(J, J->parent);
2619 TraceNo root = T->root ? T->root : J->parent;
2620 J->cur.root = (uint16_t)root;
2621 J->cur.startins = BCINS_AD(BC_JMP, 0, 0);
2622 /* Check whether we could at least potentially form an extra loop. */
2623 if (J->exitno == 0 && T->snap[0].nent == 0) {
2624 /* We can narrow a FORL for some side traces, too. */
2625 if (J->pc > proto_bc(J->pt) && bc_op(J->pc[-1]) == BC_JFORI &&
2626 bc_d(J->pc[bc_j(J->pc[-1])-1]) == root) {
2627 lj_snap_add(J);
2628 rec_for_loop(J, J->pc-1, &J->scev, 1);
2629 goto sidecheck;
2630 }
2631 } else {
2632 J->startpc = NULL; /* Prevent forming an extra loop. */
2633 }
2634 lj_snap_replay(J, T);
2635 sidecheck:
2636 if (traceref(J, J->cur.root)->nchild >= J->param[JIT_P_maxside] ||
2637 T->snap[J->exitno].count >= J->param[JIT_P_hotexit] +
2638 J->param[JIT_P_tryside]) {
2639 lj_record_stop(J, LJ_TRLINK_INTERP, 0);
2640 }
2641 } else { /* Root trace. */
2642 J->cur.root = 0;
2643 J->cur.startins = *J->pc;
2644 J->pc = rec_setup_root(J);
2645 /* Note: the loop instruction itself is recorded at the end and not
2646 ** at the start! So snapshot #0 needs to point to the *next* instruction.
2647 */
2648 lj_snap_add(J);
2649 if (bc_op(J->cur.startins) == BC_FORL)
2650 rec_for_loop(J, J->pc-1, &J->scev, 1);
2651 else if (bc_op(J->cur.startins) == BC_ITERC)
2652 J->startpc = NULL;
2653 if (1 + J->pt->framesize >= LJ_MAX_JSLOTS)
2654 lj_trace_err(J, LJ_TRERR_STACKOV);
2655 }
2656#if LJ_HASPROFILE
2657 J->prev_pt = NULL;
2658 J->prev_line = -1;
2659#endif
2660#ifdef LUAJIT_ENABLE_CHECKHOOK
2661 /* Regularly check for instruction/line hooks from compiled code and
2662 ** exit to the interpreter if the hooks are set.
2663 **
2664 ** This is a compile-time option and disabled by default, since the
2665 ** hook checks may be quite expensive in tight loops.
2666 **
2667 ** Note this is only useful if hooks are *not* set most of the time.
2668 ** Use this only if you want to *asynchronously* interrupt the execution.
2669 **
2670 ** You can set the instruction hook via lua_sethook() with a count of 1
2671 ** from a signal handler or another native thread. Please have a look
2672 ** at the first few functions in luajit.c for an example (Ctrl-C handler).
2673 */
2674 {
2675 TRef tr = emitir(IRT(IR_XLOAD, IRT_U8),
2676 lj_ir_kptr(J, &J2G(J)->hookmask), IRXLOAD_VOLATILE);
2677 tr = emitir(IRTI(IR_BAND), tr, lj_ir_kint(J, (LUA_MASKLINE|LUA_MASKCOUNT)));
2678 emitir(IRTGI(IR_EQ), tr, lj_ir_kint(J, 0));
2679 }
2680#endif
2681}

2685#undef emitir
